title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar; stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple coffeecake
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the stick of margarine and the cup of sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Add the vanilla.

title: festive cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in nuts.
Beat eggs slightly.
Combine with oil, extract, bananas and undrained pineapple.
Add to dry ingredients; mix thoroughly, but do not beat.
Spoon into well oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand.

title: sweet rolls(easy)
directions: Put pecans in bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Put rolls on top (about 24 frozen).
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon and pour over rolls.
Cover and let sit 12 hours on counter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: asparagus with nut butter sauce
directions: Cook and drain asparagus.
Melt butter; stir in lemon juice and salt.
Add pecans and saute 5 minutes.
Serve over asparagus with lemon twist.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, soda, salt and margarine, using a pastry blender to form crumbs.
Press half of this mixture into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: torte "bird's milk"
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in a mixer until well blended.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the last 4 ingredients to the mixture and beat well.
Divide the mixture into 3 equal parts in 3 (9-inch) greased and floured pans or spring-form pans.
Bake at 325° until golden brown, about 20 to 30 minutes depending on oven.

title: mom mercer's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart baking dish. Sift dry ingredients together in a mixing bowl. Add milk and stir into a batter. Pour this mixture over melted margarine. Pour fruit over the batter and bake 1 hour at 300°. The batter will rise to the top and the fruit will be on the bottom.

title: date balls
directions: Place dates, margarine, salt, egg and vanilla in saucepan. Cook 10 minutes; cool.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Grease hands and roll into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: cheese spread
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix all together using as much milk as needed for spreadability.
Use electric mixer.

title: peanut butter dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 300° and cool.

title: glazed peach pie
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in 3 medium peeled and mashed peaches and water.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes, remove from heat.
Cover surface with plastic wrap; cool.
Spread 1/4 cup mixture in bottom of baked pie shell, reserve 1/3 cup of the mixture; set aside.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a mixer bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour to cream mixture alternately with 7-Up, beating after each addition.
Stir in lemon flavor and beat well.
Pour mixture into a greased and lightly floured 10-inch tube cake pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.

title: glazed pineapple fingers
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients.
Cut in shortening. Mix egg and crushed
pineapple	together and add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moist.
Shape into bars on cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes. Top with glaze made with confectioners sugar.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake according to package.
After cake is cooled, pour strawberry glaze over top and spread over cake.
Sprinkle cut strawberries over top of glaze.
Chill.
When ready to serve, put 1 tablespoon of Cool Whip over each piece of cake.

title: potato soup
directions: Put potatoes and onion in water; cook 20 minutes.
Mix sour cream, flour, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream mixture, milk, bouillon, butter and celery.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Cook over low 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan plus 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix zucchini, sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes. Combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to first mix.
Blend well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Check at 40 minutes, may be done early.
Enjoy.
It is so good.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Cook, rinse in cold water and drain Macaroni.
In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, dill, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni, cucumber, tomatoes and onions; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill. Makes 6 cups.

title: perky peas and potatoes
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Add peas and potatoes.
Heat on stove top in double boiler or in a casserole dish in oven.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together and pour into graham cracker shell.
Chill. Toppings of your choice may be added.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and add onion and celery.
Cook slightly and add to remaining ingredients.
Pour into oblong baking dish and cook 45 to 60 minutes.
Delicious!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Put in a medium size bowl.
Add other dry ingredients and mix well.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill for several hours.

title: scallops sauteed in garlic butter
directions: In saucepan, heat margarine and garlic slowly.
Discard garlic.
Add scallops and cook 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper and serve with tartar sauce and lemon wedges.
Serves 4.

title: crock-pot mac 'n cheese
directions: Toss macaroni in vegetable oil in crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Cook, covered, on low for 3 to 5 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: marble fudge
directions: Microwave chips and marshmallows for 5 minutes on Medium. Fold in peanuts and peanut butter.
Butter a large Pyrex pan. Chill.
Cut before fudge hardens too much.

title: tex-mex bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine corn chips, egg and water. Press into 9-inch pie plate or casserole.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: corn corn muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tin.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except the cheese.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Mixture scorches easily.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan; cool and cut into squares.

title: muffin mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients with pastry blender until evenly mixed.
Store in large airtight container in refrigerator for 10 to 12 weeks.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add milk (alternate with dry ingredients).
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: very basic tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and chill.
Serve on sandwiches or stuffed in a tomato.
Yields 8 servings.

title: gourmet sauce-in a stick mix
directions: Microwave butter in glass bowl 1/2 to 1 minute or until softened.
Mix in dry milk, flour, bouillon, garlic salt, thyme and pepper.
Stir in sherry until mix is moistened and can be formed into a ball.
Shape dough into an 8-inch roll on waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Make indentations at 1-inch intervals, dividing roll into eighths.
Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.
Yields 4 cups (8 recipes).

title: snack size apple pie
directions: Open and separate the refrigerator biscuits.
Press each biscuit into a flat 4-inch circle.
Combine the cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg in a bowl or small plate.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of apple on top of each flattened biscuit.
Now spoon on 1 teaspoon of the sugar mixture on top of each biscuit.
Fold the dough on each biscuit in half over the filling, making a half circle out of each.
Preheat your oven to 375°.
Next brush each side of the folded biscuits with the melted butter.
Now dip or "dust" each biscuit in the remaining sugar mixture and place on a large cookie sheet.
Put into your oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
These are really tasty!
Makes 8 to 10 snacks.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 250° until done.
Turns out really good without the nuts.
Really moist!

title: edola's never fail chocolate icing
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add vanilla and milk.
Cook until slightly thick.
Beat a little after removing from heat.
Pour on cake while icing is still warm.

title: worms in mud
directions: Cut 1/3 off the top of oranges.
Scoop out the fruit.
Reserve the "cups" (the bottoms).
Make chocolate pudding according to directions on package.
Pour cool pudding into orange cups.
Let gummy worms dangle out of the chocolate "mud, " 4 in each cup. Great for Halloween dessert!

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Combine egg, broccoli, corn, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in small saucepan; stir in stuffing.
Combine 3/4 cup stuffing mixture with vegetable mixture.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chili casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients. Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Use large tomatoes; put salt and pepper in the flour.
Roll tomatoes in flour and drop in hot oil.
Fry until brown.

title: cheddar apple bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Beat in apple pie filling.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add sifted dry ingredients, cheese and nuts to batter.
Mix quickly and pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: instant potato salad
directions: Heat water and milk in heavy saucepan to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add potato flakes, cream cheese and remaining ingredients. Stir until blended.
Cover and keep warm.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder and shortening.
Mix by hand; add buttermilk slowly as you knead dough.
Flour board and roll out dough.
Cut out biscuits and put on greased sheet; bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend at medium speed with electric mixer until blended. Serve with bite size pieces of fresh fruit or pound cake.

title: ky. butter cake(don't even "think" about calories)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs to butter and sugar mixture, one at a time and beat well.
Add alternately 1 cup buttermilk and flour mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: easy pastry - double crust
directions: Mix flour and salt. Beat oil and milk together. Add all at once to flour. Mix lightly with fork. Divide in half. Roll between sheets of waxed paper.

title: baked steak
directions: Layer steak in baking dish.
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Add bell pepper and onion rings.
Cover and bake at 250° for 4 hours.
If liquid gets low, add more ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Keep it juicy.

title: opp-fried rattlesnake
directions: Soak snake pieces in buttermilk for at least four hours. Remove and salt and pepper to taste.
Batter in flour and deep fry in vegetable oil until golden brown.

title: creamettes lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain. Add tomato sauce and Italian seasoning. Simmer slowly for 20 to 25 minutes. Prepare lasagna according to package directions. Drain. Arrange 1 layer of lasagna in parallel strips in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Top with 1/3 of meat sauce, 1/3 Mozzarella and 1/3 cottage cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: hominy grits
directions: Boil grits in water for 5 minutes.
Drain off water and add garlic cheese, oleo and egg.
Stir.
Pour into casserole dish which has been greased.
Cover with chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in pan; cook 5 minutes after it boils. Pour on bread pudding. Very good in winter.

title: potato salad
directions: Sprinkle cooked and sliced potatoes with sugar and vinegar and add onions, celery, pickle, salt, celery salt and mayonnaise. Toss until blended. Carefully blend in eggs and chill.

title: ham and cheese biscuit sticks
directions: Preheat oven.
Mix baking mix, milk, ham and cheese until soft dough forms; beat vigorously.
Turn onto surface well floured and knead.
Pat or roll dough into rectangle (10 x 6-inch).
Cut crosswise into ten 1-inch strips.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush strips with margarine.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 biscuit sticks.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Prepare
topping
mix with milk and vanilla as directed on package.
Whip cheese until soft, beat in sugar, then blend in topping.
Pour
into crust; scoop out center and mound high at edges;
refrigerate.
Dissolve
gelatin
in boiling water. Drain berries,
measuring
syrup	and enough water to make 1/2 cup. Stir
strawberries	into
gelatin.	Chill
until syrupy. Spoon gelatin
into pie shell, leaving a narrow rim of filling around edge.
Chill until set, about 3 hours.

title: roast leg of lamb, sicilian style
directions: Mix together diced Prosciutto ham, rosemary, salt, pepper, parsley and garlic.
Wipe the leg of lamb and cut slits all over with a sharp knife.
Stuff each slit with the ham mixture, then push
a 1/2 x 1/2-inch slice of cheese into each slit.
Rub the lamb with oil (olive oil is best).
Rub salt, pepper, oregano and garlic powder all over the lamb.
Place in a greased baking pan and add the water.
Roast in a 375°
oven for approximately 30 minutes per pound until lamb is tender, basting occasionally.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix these ingredients and pour into ungreased 8 x 12-inch pan. Then mix 1/2 cup brown sugar with 1/2 cup chopped pecans, sprinkle over top of cake.
Bake in slow oven 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oriental salad(out of this world)
directions: Brown almonds and sesame seed in margarine; cool.
Mix uncooked and crumbled noodles, cabbage (or coleslaw mix) and cooled nut mixture.
Combine seasoning package from noodles with oil and sugar.
Toss with cabbage mixture at last minute and serve. Cooked, cubed chicken can also be added with oil mixture.

title: berlie's chow chow
directions: Chop the first 5 ingredients all fairly fine. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook until it comes to a good boil.
Can and seal.

title: twinkie cake(no bake)
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, cut Twinkies in half.
Layer in pan, cream side up.
Drain pineapple and put over Twinkies.
Cut bananas and cover pineapple.
Mix pudding according to package directions and pour over all.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: parisian vegetable soup
directions: Cook vegetables in 2 cups water.
Don't drain.
Melt butter and oleo in large kettle and add the chopped celery and onion. Saute until clear.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add 4 crushed bouillon cubes.
Add 6 cups cold milk.
Stir until smooth, but don't boil.
Add vegetables and liquid from vegetables.
Add 1 cup diced ham, 1 teaspoon Accent, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat thoroughly, but don't boil.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix in a crock-pot and cook at least 4 hours on low.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables according to package directions; drain. Add next 4 ingredients; mix well. Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over top; drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Simmer all ingredients together for 1/2 hour.
Pour over skinned chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake until chicken is tender. Baste a couple times while baking.
Uncover last 30 minutes, baste, brown.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in a large, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle onion rings on top; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crispy baked chicken(low cholesterol)
directions: Stir together flour and spices.
Coat chicken with mixture. Lightly oil a jelly roll pan and arrange chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake another 25 minutes.
If pan is lined with foil, clean up is easy.

title: mexican chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of an 8 x 11-inch baking dish. Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Heat in microwave just long enough to melt cheese.

title: easy chocolate fondue
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. Stir and serve with fresh fruit.

title: lazy man's pie
directions: Melt 3/4 stick butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour (2) cans cherry pie filling over batter.
Pour batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat with mixer.
Add 7-Up last.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pepper bake
directions: Cut top from peppers.
Cut down one side and remove seeds. Pour oil in glass 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Add peppers, turning to coat (you may need more oil).
Cover peppers with cheese slices. Sprinkle with dressing mix until well covered.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until peppers are soft.

title: lemon chicken salad
directions: Mix mayo, basil, juice and peel in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Serve on lettuce lined platter. Makes 4 servings.

title: southern pork chops
directions: Brown chops in pan.
Add soup and water.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.

title: corn doggie
directions: Roll hot dog in flour; be sure they are dried before frying.

title: toppie bars
directions: Put margarine, butter and brown sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Line 2 cookie sheets with graham crackers; pour ingredients over graham crackers and spread.
Preheat oven to 325°; bake for 10 minutes.
Cool in freezer for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Break apart; put on Saran Wrap in layers in a square plastic container.
Then put in freezer for better taste until ready to serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling and pineapple in pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Stir to mix.
Sprinkle dry mix evenly over filling.
Sprinkle nuts over this.
Slice oleo thin and cover dry mix with slices.
Bake at about 350° about 45 minutes until brown and done.

title: popcorn crunch
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and syrup in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook to soft crack stage (290°).
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla

title: dirt cups
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies. Place 1 tablespoon cookies in the bottom of a 6 ounce cup. Whip the pudding mix with 1 cup cold milk. Add the Cool Whip, as much as desired.
Add remaining cookie crumbs to mixture. Spoon into cups.
Decorate with gummy worms and enjoy!

title: oyako domburi
directions: Drain 1 can slivered bamboo shoots.
Put in saucepan.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil and drain.
Simmer chicken in broth for 5 minutes.
Add bamboo shoots, round onion slices, salt, sugar, shoyu and mirin.
Add green onions.
Pour beaten eggs over chicken mixture.
Cook over low flame for 30 seconds with cover on.
Serve in individual bowls over hot rice.
Garnish with crushed, toasted nori (seaweed) if desired.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Mix soup, oil, vinegar, seasonings and sugar; heat until sugar dissolves.
Pour over carrots, onion and green pepper.
Stir occasionally.
Chill 8 hours.

title: imitation guacamole
directions: In a small bowl, mash cactus with fork.
Do not blend or process.
Place asparagus in blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Add to cactus with remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips. Place mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: princess loaf
directions: Chop onion and braise in margarine.
Blend in other ingredients and bake in oiled 6 x 7-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake on hot griddle like pancakes. Good with syrup.

title: hot spice percolator punch
directions: Place fluid parts in percolator.
Place all spices and sugar in filter basket and perk.

title: oklahoma chile beans
directions: Simmer about 1 hour and then continue to cook slowly until beans are done.
Cook beans slowly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: serbian spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: calico coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, onions, peas, bacon bits and Parmesan cheese.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well. Chill for several hours before serving.

title: fudge
directions: Use 2 (9 x 13) pans.

title: zesty meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add everything, but ground beef. Mix well.
Add beef mix again.
Shape into balls.
Place in 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or more. Remove from oven and drain off grease.
Put all meatballs in one pan.

title: orange-coconut salad
directions: Arrange orange slices to overlap on a bed of lettuce.
Put a fluff of coconut in center.
Serve with French dressing.

title: golden granola
directions: Combine
all ingredients except raisins in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan; mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to
25 minutes
or until golden brown, stirring occasionally. Stir in raisins.
Cool.
Store in a tightly covered container. Serve with milk as cereal or as a snack.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Place rice in bottom of roaster pan.
Heat soups and milk and pour over rice.
Add one chicken; sprinkle with onion soup mix and paprika.
Bake 1 3/4 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; skin and bone and cut into pieces.
Save broth. Sauce onion and garlic in butter; add soup, chili powder, red pepper and salt.
Add sugar, Accent and 2 cups chicken broth. Simmer to blend flavors.
Add chicken and simmer 20 to 25 minutes to thicken.
Break spaghetti into 2-inch pieces.
Cook and drain. Add 1 tablespoon butter; stir into sauce.
Pour into two greased 8 x 8 -inch baking dishes.
Top, but do not cover completely, with cheese.
Bake at 325° to 350° until light brown.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Add dry ingredients until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Cover with crumb topping.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: stir-fried chicken with almonds
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite-size chunks.
In a medium bowl, combine chicken, soy sauce, sherry, marmalade, cornstarch, ginger and cayenne pepper.
Set aside.
Drain pea pods and pat dry with paper towels.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Bring to a boil; cook until broccoli is very well done.
Stir in 1/2 pound shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Blend until cheese is melted.

title: sin pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Press into an 8 x 10-inch pan. Brown lightly and cool.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in deep casserole dish.
Add milk and stir.
Add peaches or apples.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender, dice.
Mix all ingredients except cornflakes.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Mix cornflakes and oleo spread over mixture.
Bake for 30 min.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Beat pudding, milk and sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Use Pam cooking spray to lightly grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place a layer of whole crackers on bottom of pan.
Top with half of the pudding mix.
Add another layer of whole crackers. Top with remaining pudding mix.
Add another layer of whole crackers.
Ice with Chocolate Icing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add corn; mix well.
Add beaten eggs, butter and milk.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir twice during first half hour of baking.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and let stand 10 minutes. Add sugar to beaten egg in bowl.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Mix alternately with date mixture.
Stir in oil or melted shortening, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into large loaf pan (10 x 5 x 3-inch) and bake 1 hour.
Test with toothpick in middle. Freezes well.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Cook to firm ball stage. Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add gelatin gradually, beating constantly until stiff peaks form.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Turn into a serving dish and use for assorted fresh vegetables.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Stir together in a 9-inch square greased pan 3/4 cup sugar, the flour, salt, baking powder and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Stir in the milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix 1/2 cup each of white and brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Over this, pour 1 1/2 cups water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Best served warm with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and salt.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over 1 to 1 1/2 pounds of shredded cabbage.

title: clam chowder
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to boil; cook for 20 minutes.
Add the half and half.
In a skillet, saute the onions (chopped) in 1/2 stick margarine or butter.
Add to pot after 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: baked meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into meatballs.
Arrange on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake 12 minutes at 425°.
Arrange on top of tomato and basil pasta and serve.

title: greek stew
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; stirring to crumble.
Pour off excess fat.
Blend in flour.
Stir in water, Burgundy, brown sugar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and cinnamon.
Add onions, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve garnished with cheese and walnuts.

title: applesauce rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Roll out biscuits in rectangular sheet. Spread applesauce and pecans on dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Roll up dough as jelly roll; cut in 1-inch pieces.
Melt butter in deep pan.
Place cut pieces in pan.
Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Pour syrup over rolls and bake for 30 minutes.

title: custard peach pie
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and pat in pie pan.
Drain peaches, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Arrange peach slices in crust.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon over top.
Put in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Into large bowl, mix first 8 ingredients.
Make into average balls.
Layer into pressure cooker or Dutch oven.
Mix tomato paste with enough water, sweet basil or sugar, salt and pepper to just cover meatballs.
Put on lid.
Get pressure up.
Put on 15 pound pressure.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes.
Let sit until pressure goes down.

title: carolina delight cookies
directions: Mix together milk, sugar, cocoa and butter well.
Bring to a boil, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Let set until cooled.
Remove and store in containers.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Beat the egg yolk in a small bowl.
Blend in the molasses. Add the boiling water with the soda dissolved in it.
Set aside.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Chill.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: texas apple cake
directions: Sift the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Cream the oil, sugar and egg.
Fold the dry sifted ingredients into the creamed mixture alternately with the apples and vanilla, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add the pecans.
Turn into a buttered 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
No icing is needed.

title: chocolate slush
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and nuts until crumb-like.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on cooled crust.

title: hawaiian barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl.
Makes about 2 1/3 cups.

title: pecan raisin muffins
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, raisins and vanilla.
Blend in pecans, sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Spoon in lined muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: butter balls in chicken broth butter glase
directions: Put bread crumbs in large bowl.
Add eggs, allspice and melted butter.
Mix well.
If mixture appears too dry to form into balls, add up to 1/4 cup of chicken broth or milk.
Form into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on baking sheet and chill for at least 1 hour.
Bring broth to boil over high heat in Dutch oven.
Add some of the butter balls as broth continues to boil.
They will rise to the top when done, about 10 minutes.
Remove them with slotted spoon and place them in a bowl.
Add more butter balls and repeat procedure.
Return the cooked balls to the soup, heat and serve.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain. Add soups and simmer. Place in casserole dish. Put Tater Tots on top (enough to cover). Heat at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cornbread turkey dressing
directions: Soak cornbread and biscuits in chicken broth, getting out all lumps.
Add well beaten eggs, celery seed, black pepper, salt and chopped onions to cornbread mixture.
Grease pan.
Pour in dressing.
Cook in 425° oven about 1 hour, depending on thickness. Test for doneness with knife. Will serve 60 to 75 people (recipe divides easily).

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake rolls that have been placed in a cookie sheet (with sides) according to directions on container.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley together and spread over cooled crust.
Chop or shred vegetables and layer over mixture by sprinkling on.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Cut into whatever size squares you like.

title: taste of heaven cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Add jello pudding to cake batter, mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 inch pan and bake at 400°, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cake is done if toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in plate.
Top with chilies.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour on top of beef mixture.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes well and let bake until soft. Remove and crush them up. Add olive oil, salt and pepper and they're ready to eat.

title: tangy oven barbecued chicken
directions: Line an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with aluminum foil; set aside.
Combine first 4 ingredients in container of an electric blender.
Top with cover and process until mixture is smooth. Brush mixture evenly over both sides of chicken; reserve remaining mixture.
Place chicken, bone side up, in prepared dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.
Turn chicken and brush with remaining cranberry mixture.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Cream together and shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans or chopped parsley if desired.

title: beet salad
directions: Dice beets finely and mix with dry jello.
Bring other ingredients to a full boil and pour over beets; mix well.
Pour into a large dish and gel.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into 9 inch pie shell.
Bake 425 degrees for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350 degrees.
Bake 45 minutes or until a knife is inserted in the center and comes out clean.

title: chicken divan(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Lay broccoli spears over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Lay chicken over top.
Mix soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Beat well until blended.
Pour over top of chicken.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: cocktail nibbles
directions: Start oven at 225°.
Mix cereals, etc. in large pan.
Melt butter, add seasonings.
Pour over mix.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour, covered, and 1 hour, uncovered.
Stir occasionally.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Put marrow bone and soup meat in pot with cold water to cover. Add celery stalks, onion and carrots.
Let cook 1 hour or so, then add to broth the cabbage, tomatoes, lemon juice, brown sugar and salt and pepper.
Cook 2 hours or so.
Then enjoy.

title: slow-cooker enchiladas
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion and green pepper until beef is browned and vegetables are tender; drain. Add beans, tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine cheese.

title: pineapple ring a lings
directions: Drain the pineapple slices, and beat egg slightly; crush the zwieback or bread to make 1 cup crumbs.
Dip pineapple slices first in egg, then in crumbs.
Fry in melted butter or margarine until crisp and golden on both sides.
Serve hot.
This especially good with ham.

title: caramel custard
directions: Grease 8 custard cups.
Place 1/3 cup sugar in skillet and heat very slowly until caramel colored syrup.
Immediately pour into greased custard cups.
Start oven at 300°.
Beat the eggs until bubbly, then beat in remaining 2/3 cup sugar and the salt. Heat the milk until a film forms across the top.
Add the vanilla and stir until the vanilla is well mixed.
Slowly stir into egg mixture.
Strain and pour into the custard cups, filling them to about 1/2-inch of top.
Set the cups in a pan of warm water and bake for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Chill and unmold.
Serves 8.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash grapes and dry. Mix together remaining ingredients. Layer grapes and mixture in a bowl, beginning with the grapes. Top with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Blend in strawberries, drained pineapple and bananas.
Blend in Cool Whip and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch dish and freeze.
Thaw a little before serving.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil; add flour and mix into a ball.
Let cool.
Then add eggs, one at a time, until beaten. Spread mixture on bottom and sides of greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fudge
directions: *Set marshmallow cream in warm water when beginning to make fudge.

title: crunchy baked bananas
directions: Peel bananas and cut lengthwise; arrange in a buttered dish. Sprinkle on the brown sugar and then the marshmallows.
Mix together cornflakes and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cajun crawfish cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in small bowl.
In another bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Blend dry ingredients into all others, mixing well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan (may be sprayed with a lo-cal spray such as Pam).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except raw vegetables; let stand overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: chicken liver pate(splurge)
directions: Saute onions in 8 teaspoons of butter until golden (about 5 minutes).
Add mushrooms and chicken livers; cook, stirring occasionally, until livers are tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of butter, salt and peppers.
Stir until butter melts.
Then divide into 4 equal parts.
In blender, at high speed, puree liver mixture, one part at a time, adding 2 of the egg quarters to each part.
Turn into bowl, add nuts and mix well.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: sweet sour spareribs(serves 6)
directions: Separate spareribs and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle generously with brown sugar.
Cover with sliced onion. Mix together soy sauce, vinegar, water and cornstarch and pour this mixture over spareribs.
Cover and bake at 425° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove cover and continue baking for approximately 5 minutes to brown.
Serve sauce over rice.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut beef, pork and turkey into 1/2-inch cubes.
Dice potatoes and carrots into 1/2-inch cubes.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 4 hours with enough water to almost cover contents.

In another container, boil pearled barley in 4 cups water for 30 minutes. Dice both bell peppers, celery and onions into 1/4-inch pieces. Cut green onions into 1/4-inch pieces from the base to nearly the top of the stems.
Completely cook and drain bacon and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
At the end of cooking the beef, pork, turkey, potatoes and carrots, put all ingredients except frozen vegetables into stock pot or Dutch oven.
Put in oven at 250° for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Further season to taste.

title: meat loaf with topping
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Put in loaf pan. Pour topping over meat and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fish creole(microwave)
directions: Mix all together and pour over fish in a 1-quart dish.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap, venting one corner.
Cook on High 8 to 10 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn in four minutes.
Let stand five minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Save 1/2 of the peanuts.
Mix remaining ingredients together and make into mound.
Use the remaining peanuts to cover outside of mound.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Place all ingredients except nuts in a mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on wire rack.

title: golden fish filets
directions: In a bowl beat Eggs.
In another bowl combine next five ingredients.
Dip fillets in egg, then coat with cornmeal mixture. Heat Oil in skillet.
Fry Fish over medium heat for about 3 - 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easy with a fork.
Yield 4 servings.

title: snappy barbecue sauce
directions: In
a
saucepan
combine catsup, water, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire
sauce, salt, celery seed and hot pepper sauce. Bring
the catsup mixture to boiling;
reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.	Use to baste pork, beef or poultry during
the
last
to
20 minutes of barbecuing.
Pass any remaining sauce.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables, then add green pepper, onion and celery.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture.
Marinate overnight, then drain liquid and eat!

title: clam chowder
directions: Have potatoes cooled and put aside.
Saute bacon until crisp; set aside.
Add onion to pan and saute until soft, not brown. Stir in flour into pan and blend well.
Stir in clams and the liquid.
Heat mixture, then put into a large pot.
Stir in potatoes.
Stir constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Add in bacon bits. Reduce heat to low.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix and shape into balls. Cook in hot oil.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter 3 large loaf pans or 8 mini loaf pans and dust with flour.
Sift flour, cornstarch, baking soda and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar together with electric beater until light and lemon colored, about 3 minutes.
Add bananas, eggs and sour cream and continue to beat until smooth.
Combine flour mixture with banana mixture, but do not overbeat.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.

Pour into prepared pans and bake for 45 minutes for mini loaves, 55 minutes for large loaves or until firm in the center and edges pull away from pan. Let rest on rack for 10 minutes; remove from pans and allow to cool slightly.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add Wesson oil, then beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add 3 cups carrots (shredded).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a greased 9-inch pie dish or square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.
If using glass dish, bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 5 minutes after each at medium speed.
Do not underbeat.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill at least 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: In 4-cup glass measure, melt margarine on High for 45 seconds. Add bread crumbs, apple, raisins, salt, sugar, onion, pepper and sage, mixing lightly.
Moisten slightly with hot water.
Trim all fat from pork chops.
Place 4 chops in bottom of 8-inch microproof baking dish.
Divide stuffing into 4 portions.
Place 1 portion on top of each chop.
Cover chops with 4 remaining chops, pressing together lightly.
Sprinkle brown gravy mix over top of chops. May sift through strainer to make even layer.
Cover with wax paper and cook on Roast temperature, 14 to 18 minutes until done. Rest 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix together soup and sour cream.
Add chicken and mix well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix crushed crackers, margarine and poppy seed.
Pour over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and place half in a greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, cheese, onion and eggs.
Pour half of this mixture over broccoli.
Add remaining broccoli and top with remaining sauce.
Crush crackers and mix with butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and gently stir in eggs last.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Store covered, in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.
To bake immediately use about 3/4 cup milk.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade shake and bake chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour and seasonings in plastic bag.
Dip chicken legs in milk; shake off excess.
Add legs to bag and shake to coat evenly.
Place chicken on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake until chicken is tender and coating is crisp.
Serve with coleslaw.

title: pasta broccoli toss
directions: In large sauce pan, cook rotini as directed in boiling salt water for 6 minutes.
Add broccoli, cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain. Reserve 1/4 c. of the liquid.
Return pasta to pan.
Meanwhile heat oil in saucepan; add pepper, onion and garlic, cook about 5 minutes.
Stir in reserved liquid, salt, pepper and sugar; bring to a boil.	Pour mixture over pasta and broccoli mixture; add tomatoes, basil and cheese.
Toss and serve.
Serves 4.

title: potato kugel
directions: Grease pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours to 1 1/2 hours until brown at 350°.
Slice when cool into squares.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place sugar and vegetable oil in mixing bowl.
Cream with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Add baking powder, vanilla, cream and flour.
Mix well.
Roll the dough into 1-inch balls and space 1-inch apart.
Place on cookie sheet (nonstick); flatten with fingers.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla pudding, softened margarine, egg and milk; then pour into 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Drain peaches, saving 3 tablespoons juice.
Pat peaches dry and arrange over batter like spokes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and juice.
Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Spoon over peaches to within 1 inch of sides.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, cool 1 hour.
Refrigerate.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter, and mix real good. Add melted butter.
Place in loaf pan or mold.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: jewel-toned fruitcake
directions: Leave all ingredients whole; mix in a large bowl.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 9 x 5 x 3-inch waxed paper lined and greased pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes or until pick comes out clean.

title: tofu mayonnaise
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray oven dish or pan with Pam or line with foil.
Place pork chops in single layer in pan.
On each chop place a thin slice of onion, a thin slice of lemon, one tablespoon of catsup and one tablespoon of brown sugar.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Soften yeast in warm water with sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes or doubled in volume.
Mix next 3 ingredients together until smooth. Add yeast mixture.
Then pour into large enough container to let triple in volume (non-metal).

title: brownies
directions: Mix together.
Bake in ungreased pan (8 1/2 x 13-inch) at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin or squash cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except chocolate chips).
Put chocolate chips in last.
Do not grease sheet after first time! Cookies do not spread.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
May add 1 cup nuts with chips.

title: coconut-chocolate candy balls
directions: Blend together well all ingredients; make into balls and chill or freeze.
Then dip in a mixture of one 4 ounce cake paraffin and two 6 ounce packages of chocolate chips, melted together.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until limp.
Add garlic and rest of ingredients and serve over cooked linguini.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place breasts between sheets of waxed or plastic wrap; pound slightly.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef with enchilada mix. Add tomato sauce and water. Layer tortillas, beans and cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1/2 cup.
Combine gelatin and boiling water in electric blender. Cover and blend at low speed until dissolved (1 minute).
Add measured liquid, cream cheese and mayonnaise; cover and blend on high speed (15 seconds).
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruit.
Spoon into 6 individual molds and chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Unmold and garnish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
May need to add more flour.
Use a greased and floured pan.

title: royal cocktail
directions: Mix grape juice and sugar and pour over grapefruit pulp. Chill well, six to eight hours and arrange in iced glasses to serve.
Serves 6.

title: caramel nut roll
directions: Melt caramel pieces with butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat.
Add salt and powdered sugar alternating with milk.
Stir all the time.
Blend well after each addition.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Form in rolls and roll in nuts.
Chill overnight until ready to slice and serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Note:
If you use
frozen
blueberries, mix them with a little flour ahead of time.

title: pimiento cheese casserole
directions: Soften the
bread in milk.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour
into
a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: crab delights
directions: Place cream cheese on bed of lettuce.
Top with cocktail sauce and crab delights.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: shells and sauce
directions: Cook shells; brown hamburg, then layer shells, hamburg, pepperoni, sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Layer in a baking dish or cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese melts.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar, butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix milk, coconut and pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter; spread over top; cool.
Cut into bars.

title: omelet
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat slightly.
Melt butter; add egg mixture.
Cook over low heat until set but top is still shiny.
Lift omelet.
Let egg mixture flow below omelet. Fold omelet in half.
Serve at once.

title: curried crab soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot; add onion and cook until wilted. Add garlic and apple. Stir, sprinkle with curry powder and flour. Add tomato and broth, stirring rapidly with whisk. When thick and smooth add salt and pepper to taste. Add crabmeat. Simmer 10 minutes. Add cream. Bring to a boil. Add shakes of Tabasco. Garnish with chopped parsley. Serves 6-8.

title: beef and squash strata(serves 6)
directions: Prepare meat sauce as directed.
Trim ends from zucchini and thinly slice on the diagonal.
Stir-fry in butter 2 to 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Place in a buttered 10-inch round baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with garlic salt.
Spoon meat sauce over zucchini. Cover with a layer of tomatoes.
Beat cottage cheese and eggs together.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, Gruyere and onions.
Pour over tomatoes.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Cut into wedges.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan.
Drain grease.
Add chili seasoning to taste.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with 1/2 ground beef mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Drain juice from kidney beans and spread over cheese.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover beans and cheese with tortilla chips.
Cover chips with remaining ground beef, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with diced tomatoes, then add onion (if desired).
Cover with lettuce. Decorate with black olives, remaining tortilla chips and dollops of sour cream as desired.

title: best ever pork and beans
directions: Mix all ingredients into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
To serve, let it soften and put into a very small, hulled out pumpkin with gingersnap cookies around the pumpkin.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple and fold in all ingredients. Chill!

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, raisins and onion.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli and toss to cool.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, sprinkle with pecans and bacon.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Melt both chocolates in a pan (over hot water).
Add cornflakes and nuts. Stir until flakes are thoroughly coated. Place by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or aluminum foil to harden. The one pound Hershey bar works best for the sweet chocolate.

title: baked carp
directions: Fillet carp as usual.
Measure width and length of each fillet.
Cut a pine board just slightly larger than fillet.
Put pine board between fillets; salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap in tinfoil.

title: quicky carbonara
directions: Saute garlic and ham in oil and butter.
Add the cooked spaghetti, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir well and turn heat off.
Beat eggs and pour over spaghetti.
Quickly toss to coat.
Add olives; toss again and serve.
This can be transferred to a large baking dish and baked in a 350° oven for 15 minutes, if desired.
Can also be doubled.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut venison into thin strips.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over meat.
Marinade overnight.
Pat meat dry and place on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Preheat oven at 150°.
Place cookie sheet in oven with the oven door slightly open.
Dry meat 4 to 6 hours.
Jerky may also be put in dehydrator.

title: heavenly jam
directions: Combine all except jello; have a high heat until it boils; reduce heat and boil 20 minutes.
Stir in jello until dissolved; remove from heat; put in jars and seal.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread according to directions on box.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in greased casserole dish, 11 x 13-inch.

title: pork chop with sauerkraut
directions: Rinse the sauerkraut in water and drain.
Cut the potatoes in half.
Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Sprinkle the chops with salt and pepper and brown on both sides. Remove.
Put potatoes in the same pan, cut side down and brown. Remove.
Pour in the water and scrape up any browned bits on the bottom of pan.
Add sauerkraut, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and the caraway.
Top with chops and potatoes, pressing them into the sauerkraut.
Lower the heat, cover the pan and simmer until the chops are very tender, about 40 minutes.

title: macaroni and pea dish(diet dish)
directions: Melt butter in top of boiler.
Combine salt and onions.
Add milk and flour; cook until thick.
Put all ingredients into a baking dish.
Cook for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients;
set
aside.
Beat
butter, shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields approximately 6 dozen.

title: toffee butter crunch(candy)
directions: Butter sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In saucepan, melt 1 cup Food Lion butter; add water, sugar and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat to 290°, stirring frequently.
(Mixture should boil gently over entire surface.)
Watch carefully after 280°; remove from heat.
Immediately pour over parchment paper.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes.
Soften chocolate in small saucepan; spread evenly over toffee and sprinkle chopped pecans over chocolate.
Let stand overnight; break into pieces.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 pounds.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in mixing bowl. Pour into greased crock-pot. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: sugarless noodle kugel(great for easter)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix margarine and eggs until smooth. Blend in cheese, sour cream, raisins, sweetener and cinnamon.
Mix in cooked noodles. Spoon mixture into sprayed (with cooking spray) 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake Kugel uncovered until heated through, about 45 to 55 minutes. Cut into squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: five hour stew
directions: Place all ingredients in 5-quart Dutch oven, using enough V-8 juice to cover meat and vegetables.
Mix, cover and place in oven at 250° and cook for 5 hours.

title: date bars
directions: Melt oleo and Crisco.
Put all dry ingredients in a large bowl. Pour melted oleo on top of mixed dry ingredients and stir until mixed well.
Put half into a 9 x 9-inch pan and press down.
Pour in Date Filling and spread evenly.
Top with the rest of the oat mixture and press lightly.
Cook for 20 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: tamale dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Mash with potato masher until well blended.
Heat in crock-pot until melted; stir occasionally.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: curried potatoes
directions: Peel, dice and cook the potatoes.
Melt margarine and add remaining ingredients.
Layer potatoes and sauce in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: celery pie
directions: Trim and cut celery into 2-inch lengths.
Put into pot with chopped onion and enough water to cover; add salt and simmer until tender.
Melt margarine in separate pan.
Add flour, then milk and 4 ounces of stock and stir until boiling.
Season to taste and mix with chopped, hard-boiled egg.
Layer celery in a greased pie plate and pour sauce over.
Mix mashed potatoes with cheese; season and spread over celery.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: salmon loaf or patties
directions: Mix well, grease loaf pan and bake in oven for 1 hour at 340°. Or brown in Pam-sprayed frying pan.

title: spinach dip #2
directions: Cook spinach as directed; squeeze dry.

title: beef sandwiches
directions: To minced cold roast beef, add the salt, tomato catsup, Worcestershire sauce and melted butter.
Spread on buttered bread; cover with a second slice and cut into fancy shapes.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Double for 1 chicken.

title: soup tortellini
directions: Brown sausage in a large pot separating into small pieces. Saute onion and garlic.
Add beef broth, water, wine, carrots, basil, oregano, tomatoes, tomato sauce, parsley and peppercorns. Simmer 1 hour.
Add zucchini and tortellini and simmer 30 to 40 more minutes.
Add chickpeas and green beans the last 10 minutes.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Serve over fresh spinach with crumbled bacon and hard boiled eggs.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar.
Take off stove and add oil.
Pour over kraut mixture and toss.

title: spinach salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in order given.
Top with sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Seal in airtight container. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in the bottom of baking dish.
Pour mixed vegetables over the top of chicken, then cover with soup and broth.
Mix Bisquick, milk and margarine together and pour over the top.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato fritters
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, sugar, milk and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Sift flour and measure.
Add to the first mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in beaten egg whites.
Drop by teaspoon into deep-fat (365°).
Fry until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 10 servings.

title: meat loaf balls
directions: Mix hamburger, bread, salt, pepper, onions, green peppers and catsup together.
Form into balls and place in pan.
Pour Ragu spaghetti sauce over balls and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Makes 16 medium size balls.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directions state on box in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Drain pineapple; spread over cooled cake.
Top with cream cheese mixture, then Cool Whip. Garnish with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Heat cranberry juice and strain.
Set berries aside.
Dissolve gelatin in hot juice and water.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Chill until thickened enough to mound when dropped from spoon.
With rotary beater, beat in mayonnaise until light and fluffy.
Fold in the cranberries, fruit and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold at serving time.

title: illiria bean soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, saute onion and garlic in a little oil. Add remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: kahlua cream colada
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, green beans, celery, green pepper, onion, grated cheese, sour cream and cream of celery soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix Ritz crackers and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Place sugar, evaporated milk and butter in saucepan; bring to boil for 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
In large bowl mix German sweet chocolate, chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla. Pour milk mixture over chocolate and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix until chocolate is completely melted.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased pans and chill 12 to 24 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in covered container and chill. Roll into balls and bake at 350° until brown and done.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Cut in half lengthwise; scoop out pulp and mash or press through ricer.
Add cream of mushroom soup, margarine, salt and pepper; whip until light and fluffy while gradually adding about 1/3 cup milk.
Pile back into potato shells; sprinkle cheese over tops.
Return to hot 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or set into broiler until cheese is melted.

title: twinkie pudding
directions: Split Twinkies and line dish.
Prepare pudding mix and pour over Twinkies.
Add a layer of bananas.
Cover bananas with pineapple.
Then add whipped topping.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Mix mustard, Worcestershire sauce and garlic in a small bowl. Spread mixture on both sides of the sliced rolls.
Put ham and cheese on the rolls.
Cover with tinfoil and heat in a warm oven until the cheese has melted.
Serve warm.

title: meat loaf from heaven
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Form all ingredients into loaf except chili sauce and bacon.
Put in baking dish.
Top with chili sauce and bacon.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let sit 15 minutes before serving.

title: good frosting
directions: Mix pudding in first, then pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet.
Drain lima beans. Combine hamburger with bean mixture.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Let cook in crock-pot for 1 hour.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Proof the yeast in the warm water.
Add the salt, margarine, egg and flour.
Chill 2 to 24 hours.
Divide the dough into half. Cut each half into 16 pieces.
Roll each piece 20-inches long. Knot into pretzel shape and place on greased pan.
Blend egg yolk and water to brush on pretzels.
Sprinkle on salt.
Rise the dough 1 hour.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows; add Jell-O.
Mix thoroughly. Pour over popcorn.
Shape into balls using well-greased hands.

title: french onion soup
directions: Spray the bottom of Dutch oven with Pam.
Saute the onions in olive oil and margarine.
Stir frequently for 10 to 15 minutes. Next, add 3 cups hot water, browning sauce, beef bouillon, parsley, sugar, dried mustard and marjoram.
Cook 1 hour.
Serve over hard toasted French bread and Swiss cheese.
It's delicious!

title: mock apple pie
directions: Boil water, sugar, cream of tartar and lemon juice 1 minute. Drop in crackers (don't stir).
Pour in unbaked crust.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Strip crust.
Bake until brown.

title: mary's yellow cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes (or until cake springs back in center) in a 350° oven.
Cool, then split layers in two.
Top with Seven Minute Icing and coconut.

title: spinach pate
directions: Wash and stem spinach.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a loaf pan.
Puree spinach or chop fine.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Layer in crock-pot as follows:
noodles, sauce mixture, cheese and pepperoni.
Repeat until crock-pot is full.
Heat on low until melts.

title: lemon-orange rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake.
Cool cake in pan 15 minutes, then poke full of holes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onions in hot oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and all seasonings.
Simmer uncovered for 45 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Simmer again for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Serve over rice.
You may cover while simmering last 15 minutes.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix together and cook until clear. Makes 1 pint.

title: cold carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until just tender.
Drain and set aside to cool. Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir and add carrots.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Lasts up to two weeks.

title: beef and beans
directions: Mix pork and beans with mustard, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add to bean mixture. Pour in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute onions, sausage and garlic until onions are golden (in oil).
Pour in tomato paste, tomato sauce, mushrooms with juice and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add macaroni (precooked) and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: italian biscotti
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar, salt, vanilla and 3 tablespoons Anisette until light in color. Add gradually the flour and baking powder; mix well. Knead in chopped nuts, candied fruit, if desired. Shape into 2 loaves. Place loaves on 2 greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until golden. Cool and slice at an angle into slices. Place flat down on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, until "toasted". Sprinkle with sugar.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: In saucepan, heat to boil all ingredients, except mushrooms. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook another 3 to 5 minutes.

title: colorado pot roast
directions: Rub
flour
on	meat;
brown well on all sides in heavy kettle.
Slip
rack
under meat.
Add tomatoes, water, garlic, salt
and
pepper.	Cover;	simmer 2 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat; cover and simmer until tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
To serve, slice meat and pour sauce over it.

title: potato romanoff
directions: Peel potatoes; dice and chill.
Melt margarine in pan with cheese.
Stir until almost melted.
Remove from heat.
Add soup and stir.
Add sour cream and salt.
Lightly mix sauce with potatoes and put in 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Cover with 1 cup crushed corn flakes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: skillet chicken and peaches
directions: In a large skillet or electric frying pan heat oil.
Brown chicken.
Remove to a platter.
Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms, just until onion is limp.
Add peaches with juice. Into the water stir bouillon cube, ginger and cornstarch until dissolved.
Add to peach mix.
Simmer until mixture is thickened. Return chicken to skillet.
Cover, simmer for 25 minutes until chicken is completely cooked.
Serve over rice or egg noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Fold milk into Cool Whip and add other ingredients. Refrigerate and garnish with whole strawberries, if desired.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter.
Add milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until mixture thickens.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar; spread over pie.
Let brown.

title: beef jerky
directions: Meat has to be cut in very thin strips.
It is best to do this while meat is partially frozen.
Mix all other ingredients in very large bowl.
This is the marinade for the jerky.
Put meat into marinade mixture and marinate in refrigerator 1 day.
Take meat out of mixture and lay strips on racks of dehydrator.
This has to dehydrate for about 8 hours.
Do not overlap strips of meat on dehydrator.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Layer shrimp in large baking pan.
Add sufficient butter to cover.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until shrimp turn pink.
Place shrimp under broiler for an additional 5 to 10 minutes until exposed shrimp start to turn brown.
Serve shrimp and sauce in bowl with garlic bread for dunking.

title: cranberry salad
directions: First, grind cranberries and orange together.
Second, boil sugar and 1 cup water for 5 minutes.
Add orange and cranberries, then add jello and all other ingredients.
Set in refrigerator until well set.
May be molded or served from bowl.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Mix macaroni, onion, pimiento, grated cheese (reserve 1/4 cup), milk and mushroom soup together.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: egg in a hole
directions: Butter both sides of bread after tearing out a hole (in the center
of the slice) about the size of the egg yolk.
Put bread in frying pan and then break egg into hole.
Cook slowly and flip to
finish
cooking
egg.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine prepared vegetables in a 1-quart jar.
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate jar.
Shake vigorously to blend.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Shake jar several times to coat top vegetables with marinade.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, jello, oil and milk.
Add eggs and strawberries and beat really good.
Stir in coconut and floured nuts.
Makes a 3 layer cake.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together. Add beaten eggs, buttermilk, melted oleo and vanilla. Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable-beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in iron skillet.
Add soup; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Place biscuits on top of casserole.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 425°, until biscuits are done.
Serve immediately.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Beat all ingredients, until smooth for 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Then mix with rest of ingredients.
Put in two casseroles and bake covered for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Put chow mein noodles on top and replace in oven, uncovered, and heat through.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart square baking dish. Bake uncovered.
Serve hot or cold.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots.
Heat together soup, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire Sauce, and corn oil.
Pour over carrots.
Add bell pepper and onion, chopped.
Stores well in refrigerator.

title: black beans cuban style
directions: In a large pot, place 1 quart of water and beans.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside for 1 hour.
Discard water.
In a large pot, place beans, 1 quart water and 2 teaspoons salt or to taste.
Cook beans until tender, about 30 minutes.

title: barbara's pecan pie
directions: Melt
butter;
add corn syrup, vanilla, salt and sugar. Heat enough to make a smooth mixture, but not hot.
Beat eggs very well;
gradually
add
to
syrup mixture, blending well. Add pecans and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 35 to 55 minutes. When pie is browned and set, pie is done.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla and walnut extracts, then milk.
Add lightly beaten eggs; mix.
Add and blend walnuts into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 3 x 9-inch cake baking pans.
Bake at 375° until done (about 26 minutes).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in water.
Cool and cube in bite size pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together mushroom soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken cubes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar in covered container. Shake/mix well.
Make ahead early in day or night before.
Shake well few times during day.
Place broccoli, bacon, cheese and onion in large salad bowl.
Pour dressing over and mix well.

title: canadian cheese soup(servings:  8)
directions: Melt butter in large pot; add vegetables and cook over low heat until soft.
Add flour and cornstarch; cook until it bubbles. Stir in broth and milk (stir until smooth).
Add soda and cheese. Heat until cheese melts.
Pepper to taste.
Each serving:
245 calories, 13 grams protein, 16 grams fat.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Prepare instant pudding using only half the required milk. Fold in ice cream.
Pour into prepared, baked pie shell.
Freeze, if desired, or refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: italian chicken enchiladas
directions: In medium saucepan, heat oil.
Dice chicken into small cubes. Add to hot oil.
Sprinkle with garlic powder; saute until cooked. Add spaghetti sauce and heat.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, spoon just a couple of tablespoons into bottom of pan to keep enchiladas from sticking.
With a slotted spoon, spoon about a tablespoon of chicken and sauce onto flour tortilla shell.
Sprinkle with cheese and roll.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
When pan is full, pour remaining sauce over tortilla shells.
Sprinkle with cheese. Place in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with fork and put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool before frosting.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add gelatin and lemon juice.
Fold in Milnot.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Pat into pan and chill in refrigerator while preparing filling.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top of filling, too.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender (20 minutes).
In baking pan, rub butter in bottom of pan and sprinkle 1/2 bag of cornbread stuffing in pan.
In large bowl, place stick of butter, both cans of soup and 1 can of broth from the water you boiled the chicken in.
Mix together until butter is melted.
Shred chicken breast and mix in bowl with soup and butter.
Pour into baking pan. Sprinkle remainder of stuffing on top of chicken.
Bake t 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato until done.
Peel and mash.
In mixing bowl, add potato.
Mix with confectioners sugar until it becomes stiff. Place on wax paper and roll out like biscuit dough.
Spread peanut butter over this and roll until size you want and cut in small pieces.

title: low-fat chicken bake
directions: Place in baking dish.
Pour liquid over.
Bake at 350° with meaty side down for 45 minutes.
Turn and bake 15 more minutes. Bake, uncovered.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour mixture into pie crust and chill.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut wings apart at joints, discarding wing tips.
Combine soy sauce, pineapple juice, minced garlic and onion, ginger, brown sugar and beer.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Allow chicken to marinate in this mixture at least one hour or longer.
If chicken will be marinating longer than an hour, it is better if the green onion is not added until cooking time.

title: robert redford cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: "thumb print" cookies
directions: Add sifted powdered sugar, margarine, salt and vanilla.
Beat together until fluffy.
Stir sifted flour and pecans into bowl of powdered sugar mixture.
Mix well and chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Shape into small balls and place 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Press a small hole in the center of each ball with your thumb.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes until lightly browned.
After cookies have cooked fill the hollows with icing or jelly.
Makes 60 small cookies.

title: home-style macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook macaroni and drain.
In a 3-quart saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in flour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk, cream cheese, salt, pepper and mustard.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and Cheddar cheese.
Pour this into a 7-quart casserole dish.

title: lemonade pie(easy but delicious)
directions: In a medium-sized mixing bowl, combine lemonade with condensed milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Mix well.
Pour into crust and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
If you want topping on pie, use another 8 ounce carton of whipped topping.

title: smorbrod blacklund
directions: Spread rye bread with butter.
Cover with two layers of sliced ham.
Cover with Edam or similar hard cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese just melts.
Top each with one pineapple ring.
Decorate with sprig of fresh parsley.

title: steamed brown bread
directions: Soak crumbs in sour milk for 1/2 hour.
Add soda, salt, cornmeal and molasses.
If divided, steam 2 hours.
If not, steam 4 hours.

title: lemonade pie(quick and easy)
directions: Mix lemonade and milk.
Fold in cool whip.
Fill pie crust and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: party cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan or crock-pot.
Add milk to desired thickness.
Add hot peppers if desired.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix and drop teaspoonful on wax paper.
Let dry and then eat.

title: no cholesterol cake
directions: In mixing bowl, mix in order given.
Beat 30 to 40 strokes. Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan for 30 to 40 minutes or until done, at 350°.
Cover with Cool Whip or sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Uses no oil and no eggs.
Very good.
Will be quite moist.

title: teenager's delight
directions: Brown meat and diced onion.
Add salt.
Drain off fat and put in casserole, layering it with potatoes and soup mixed with milk. Bake covered in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover and add grated cheese.
Bake uncovered for 10 minutes.
Add onions and put in oven for 5 minutes.

title: appetizer cheese bake
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Stir in cheese and onion. Spoon into 1-quart souffle dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Serve immediately with crackers.
Yields 3 cups.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve on bread or rolls.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring to a boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour in peanut butter chips and an 8 ounce jar of marshmallow cream.
Stir together and pour in a pan.
Cool before cutting into pieces.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Bake at 425° for 20-25 minutes.

title: banana walnut cake(sugar-free)
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together mashed banana and butter until creamy.
Add eggs and water.
Beat well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth; add chopped walnuts.
Spoon batter into an oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
