Cool and cut into squares.

title: rutabaga and apple
directions: Cook rutabaga in boiling salted water for 25 minutes; drain. Place 1/2 rutabaga and 1/2 apple in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 brown sugar; dot with 1/2 butter.
Sprinkle with salt. Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Add sugar to eggs; beat well.
Stir in potatoes, butter and buttermilk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill one hour.
Roll 1/3 at a time.
Let raise 10 minutes and fry in hot oil or Crisco.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chill several hours; decorate with cherries, if desired.

title: sauteed spinach
directions: Rinse spinach thoroughly, remove tough stems and tear leaves in half.
Allow water to cling to leaves for steaming.
Melt the margarine in a large skillet.
Press garlic through a press and add to the skillet, stirring until coated with margarine.
Add spinach and soy sauce.
Stir until spinach is wilted and cooked through.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: healthy almost instant pizza
directions: Spread sauce on crust.
Add toppings.
Spread cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese is golden.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add 1 cup of chopped nuts and mix well.
Refrigerate until firm.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining nuts.
Garnish as desired.

title: adams county apple cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, 2 cups sugar, oil, eggs, orange juice, salt and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly combined.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until thickens. Add rest of ingredients.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, oil, eggs and flour.
Add baking soda, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes accordingly. Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fried potatoes with sausage
directions: Fry onion and pepper until half done; add potatoes and fry until they are done.
Add green or wax beans and continue cooking until done.
Fry sausage or kolbassi, slice and add to beans and potatoes.
Serve hot.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 1-quart baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 325° until browned and crumbly looking on top.

title: pork chop skillet
directions: In bowl of hot water, thaw unopened pouch of broccoli for 15 minutes.
Lightly sprinkle chops with ginger.
Brown in oil. Remove.

title: irish cream(like bailey's)
directions: Place in blender on medium speed for 1 minute.
Serve straight up or on the rocks.

title: my favorite barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer slowly for about 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Especially good as a basting sauce for beef, pork and poultry when cooking on the grill.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.
Any left over keeps very well in refrigerator.

title: mexican potato salad
directions: Place picante sauce, lime juice, oil, salt and pepper in a microwave-safe bowl.
Cook 40 to 60 seconds until heated through.

title: minted cucumber soup
directions: Slice cucumbers thickly.
Combine 1 1/2 cucumbers with onion, mint and broth in blender container. Process until finely chopped. Pour into serving bowl. Blend in yogurt and pepper. Chill, covered, for 1 to 2 hours.
Adjust seasonings.
Garnish with reserved finely chopped cucumbers, walnuts and freshly chopped chives.

title: diet cake
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add water to make 2 cups.
Pour over raisins and cook until liquid is gone.
Cool.
(Can be cooked ahead of time and refrigerated.)
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add soda, flour, spices, pineapple and applesauce.
Mix well.
Add raisins and orange flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Place in cold oven and set at 325°.
Bake 1 hour. Let cool.
Store in cool place.
Freezes well.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until tender.
Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, cheese, dash of pepper and cooked carrots.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Prepare pasta as directed, adding vegetables to water during last 5 minutes of pasta cooking time.
Drain.
Add cheese and toss until melted.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream
butter,	shortening
and
sugar	until light and fluffy.
Add
eggs, beaten until a lemon color.
Mix flour and baking
powder
and
add
to
creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir
in flavorings and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool but do not turn out of pan.

title: hot and creamy veg dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 quart casserole combine vegetable soup mix, Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup Monterey Jack cheese and bacon. Top with remaining Monterey Jack cheese and bake uncovered 30 minutes until heated through.
Makes 2 1/2 cups dip.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions, peppers and mushrooms in butter.
Add:
drained hominy, Cheez Whiz, olives and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sweet cabbage slaw
directions: Combine first three ingredients in bowl.
Heat sugar in juice until dissolved, then stir in mayonnaise.
Pour over cabbage mixture and stir well.

title: french meat pie
directions: Put meat, onion and celery in pan, break up meat as you are simmering.
Add approximately 1 cup of water and cover.
Simmer low until celery is softened.
Strain meat but keep the juice aside.
Spoon filling into 2 inch pie crusts.
Fill full.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons of juice over filling.
Add top crust.
Cut several slits in top.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown.
You may freeze pies uncooked.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients in order given.
Layer of cherries, layer of pineapple, layer of cake mix, melted margarine, layer of coconut and layer of nuts.
Do not mix.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until cake is brown, or seems to be done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first nine ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour into a large shallow baking dish.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Just before baking cover with the potato chips and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot. Serves 8.

title: salad delight
directions: In large bowl, mix together cottage cheese, strawberry jello, pineapple, pecans and strawberries.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in large casserole.
Place in refrigerator for an hour or so.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine to boil over medium heat for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: tomato bread(best when tomatoes are homegrown)
directions: Cut a loaf of French or Italian bread in half, then slice in half lengthwise.
Add garlic salt, onion salt, thinly sliced tomatoes (overlapping a little), salt and pepper.
Add oregano, Mozzarella cheese, parsley and pepperoni (optional).
Bake at 350° until the cheese melts.
Delicious!

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt margarine with sugar in large bowl and add beaten eggs.
Add yeast and water, stir in flour until well mixed.
Place in light bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: salmon spread
directions: Blend together gelatin and water.
Add cream cheese, mayo, vinegar and salmon.
Blend all together and add green pepper and olives.
Blend together and pour into a 3-cup mold.
Refrigerate until set.
Unmold and sprinkle with paprika.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain in morning.
Cover with water; parboil gently for 45 minutes.
Use the soda as beans come to boil, remove foam.
Put all other ingredients in 1 pint hot water; mix well.
Strain beans.
Put beans into pot.
Pour on flavor mix; add enough water to cover beans.
Add more as needed during baking. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Reduce heat to 275°.
Takes 8 or 9 hours.

title: peach-blackberry cobbler
directions: Thaw 4 crusts. Cut and fit 2 pie crusts into the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking pan.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Put spices and sugar in basket of 8-cup percolator.
Put water and juices in bottom of percolator.
Brew for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar well.
Add sour milk and soda dissolved in milk.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Drop on greased pans with teaspoon.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers tightly in jars.
Mix up syrup and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand for 5 days in refrigerator before eating. After opening jar, keep refrigerated.

title: pineapple turnover or apricot cake
directions: You will need a 10-inch iron skillet.

title: caroline marsh's impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together well.
Add melted margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Beat all ingredients together.
Grease (or spray with Pam) 2 pie plates and pour mixture into the 2 pie plates, dividing mixture equally.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cold it slices well and it makes its own crust!

title: spanish soup
directions: Cut beef in small pieces.
Cook until tender.
Fry onions and peppers in a saucepan.
When they are tender, add tomato sauce and soforito.
Let simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add this to the meat.
Then add other ingredients.
Cook until rice and potatoes are done.

title: tuna dip
directions: Saute onion in oleo until wilted.
Add tuna, soup and seasoning.
Serve with party crackers.

title: temptation cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box in a large oblong pan, using milk instead of water.
When done, punch holes in top with a toothpick.
Bring to a boil 2 cups sugar and pineapple; pour over cake while hot, then let cool at room temperature.
Blend together cream cheese, vanilla pudding and milk.
Pour over cooled cake and set in refrigerator until mixture thickens.
Cover with bananas and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, cherries and coconut.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix together broccoli, onion, water chestnuts, soup, and rice.
Melt Cheez Whiz and margarine.
Pour over broccoli mixture. Cover; bake at 350° 1 hour.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Set aside. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add gradually to butter mixture, beating after each addition.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Dip a flat-bottomed glass in granulated sugar and use to flatten each ball.
Insert a wooden stick into each to resemble a lollipop.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely on cookie sheets; remove carefully.
Decorate cookies as desired.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese and onion; set aside. Mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms.
Pat into pan, pressing dough 1/2 inch up sides.
Layer beef, tomatoes and green pepper on dough.
Spoon sour cream mixture on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until edges are brown.

title: cold peach soup
directions: Pour water in a saucepan.
Add cloves, sugar and cinnamon. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch solution, whipping it into the syrup with a wire whisk. Bring to a boil again.
Take off stove and stir wine and refrigerate.
Split, seed and slice enough peaches to make up two cups.
Add to syrup.
Puree the others.
Add to the syrup mixture. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: walnut pie
directions: Beat egg whites and vanilla until stiff.
Gradually add the sugars, then crushed crackers and walnuts.
Bake at 350° in a greased pie pan for 25 minutes.

title: 6 cup fruit salad
directions: Combine oranges, pineapple, coconut and marshmallows in bowl; mix well.
Fold in sour cream.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fresh banana cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add bananas, buttermilk, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until combined, then medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into long cake pan or 2 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use your favorite icing.

title: butter scones
directions: When shortening is melted, cool and add beaten eggs, yeast and water.
Mix well.
Add sugar and then flour and salt.
Beat 1 minute.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hopping john
directions: Place peas in large saucepan; cover with boiling water.
Add ham bone, onion, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour and 15 minutes until peas are done.
Arrange rice over peas; add enough water to cover rice.
Bring to boiling point; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand until rice is tender.
Stir in tomatoes. Makes 6 servings.

title: hunter's sauce
directions: Saute onions in butter; stir in and saute mushrooms.
Add wine.
Simmer until reduced to half.
Add tomato sauce and brown sauce.
Cook 5 minutes; season and add parsley.

title: spiced cranberry punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Tie spices loosely in square of cloth and drop into juices.
Put on the lid.
Heat mixture over full flame until it comes to a boil.
Reduce flame and let mixture boil gently for 3 minutes.
Remove bag of spices. Turn flame to keep warm until punch is to be served.

title: lemony cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes. Cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add egg, oil and cranberries.
Bake at 300° to 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: egg souffle
directions: Cube stale bread.
Cube Old English cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm with warm sauce of 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup sour cream.

title: e-z fried saimin
directions: Cook noodles as
directed on package, except do not add packaged flavoring.
After	noodles are done, drain water out. Cook onion	until
transparent.
Add meat and vegetables.
Add drained
noodles
to
onion,
meat	and
vegetables.
Use
the packaged flavoring that
was in saimin package and sprinkle on noodles.
Add pepper, if desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Melt the oleo in casserole dish. Pour mixture over the melted butter.
Next, pour the peaches over this, then pour 1 cup of sugar over peaches, then 3/4 cup water over sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes, or until brown.

title: my surprise
directions: Break up broccoli and cauliflower.
Cut up peppers, potatoes, onions, carrots and mushrooms into quarters.
Put in a dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise or butter to taste.
Cover with tinfoil and put in oven for 45 minutes at 375°.
You have a good dish or mixed vegetable that's easy to fix!

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare and slice potatoes.
Boil just until tender in just enough water to cover.
Drain.
Add soup, margarine and milk. Pour into greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly (about 25 minutes).
Top with grated cheese (Cheddar or Mozzarella, your preference).
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lime juice, sugar, ginger, salt and pepper. Stir in chicken, peaches and green onions; cover.
Chill before serving.
Stir in almonds.
Makes 3 cups.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° until cake tester comes out clean.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix together to make sauce the soup, sour cream, lemon juice and mayonnaise. Layer bottom to top in baking dish the broccoli, Velveeta cheese, chicken and sauce.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef, bacon and onion.
Add and mix red kidney beans, pork and beans and butter beans.
Add and mix brown sugar, white sugar, barbecue sauce, catsup, chili powder, prepared mustard and molasses.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can be frozen before or after baking.
Serves 12.

title: chicken caruso and rice
directions: Skin and bone chicken breasts.
Cut into thin strips.
Season with garlic salt and pepper.
Saute in butter 2 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and Italian seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add celery.
Continue cooking until celery is tender-crisp.
Serve over rice.

title: frozen strawberry margarita pie
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Add strawberries and fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: potted garlic chicken
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil.
Add chicken and cook about 5 minutes on each side until browned.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook over medium heat, turning chicken every 15 minutes.
Add another 1/4 cup water if needed.
Cook about 30 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serves 4.

title: butter toffee
directions: Bring sugar, salt, water and butter to boiling; add almonds. Cook, stirring constantly, to light crack stage (285°).
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
When cool, brush with chocolate and sprinkle with walnut meats.
Break into pieces. Makes about 2 dozen pieces.

title: roasted red pepper and eggplant dip with pita wedges
directions: On tray, arrange an assortment of crisp celery, carrot, cucumber and green pepper sticks, cauliflorets, cherry tomatoes, mushroom slices, radish fans, whole green onions, whole green beans and chunks of peeled zucchini.
Sprinkle with garlic or onion salt.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine applesauce and baking soda, then combine oleo and sugar.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add oil and vanilla and mix. Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add zucchini, raisins, nuts and coconut.
Bake in 2 regular size bread pans or 3 smaller size pans at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean when tested in center of loaf.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat; mix all other ingredients.
Cook 25 minutes; add cooked meat and cook 15 more minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns. Serves 8.

title: swedish kringler
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup butter and 2 tablespoons water like a pie crust.
Put on cookie sheet.
Put 1 cup water and 1/2 cup butter in saucepan and heat to boiling point.
As you remove pan from heat, add 1 cup flour and stir until smooth.
Stir in eggs, one at a time, beat after adding.
Add almond extract and spread on top of first mixture.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes in 350° oven. Cool and top with powdered sugar icing:

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into a greased dish (or Pam it). Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk, cheese, mustard and pepper.
Stir with fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth; knead gently, just until smooth. Roll out 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds with floured 2-inch cutter.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and eggs.
Add milk and jam.
Sift dry ingredients.
Roll raisins and pecans in flour mixture.
Combine all ingredients and mix together.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: 4 bean hot dish
directions: Brown bacon.
Cook onions in bacon grease.
With some grease and cooked onion, add all other seasonings.
Pour over bacon; simmer about 20 minutes.
Mix in all beans.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Freezes very well.

title: home-canned apple pie filling
directions: Blend all ingredients. Stir in 10 cups water.
Stir and cook until thick and bubbly.
Add 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Pack sliced, peeled and seeded apples in sterile quart jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Pour in syrup to 1/2-inch.
Seal and process in boiling water bath 20 minutes.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Have eggs, butter and milk at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating between each one.
Add flour that has been sifted four times alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Add lemon and vanilla extract.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix beef, onions, bread crumbs, egg, salt, ginger and milk. Shape into meatballs.

title: neva's layer salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Stir together macaroni, onions and 2 tablespoons bacon bits in a medium bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, 1/4 cup cheese, sugar and garlic powder.
In a large salad bowl or large rectangular Pyrex pan, layer salad greens, macaroni mix, cucumber, cauliflower, broccoli, radishes, tomatoes and remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Pour dressing over top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Sprinkle with bacon bits before serving.
(You may want to wait until serving to add the tomatoes.)

title: cherry delight(serves 12)
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add flour well.
Stir in nuts.
Press mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust. Chill!
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: peach salad
directions: Heat and cool jello, pineapple and sugar.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Mix meat, rice, onion, sauce, salt, pepper and garlic. Form into 8 patties; wrap with bacon and fasten with toothpick. Bake in oven at 450° for 30 minutes. Mix soup and milk. Heat, stirring often. Serve over meat.

title: uncooked mints
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Add coloring and peppermint.
Roll out; cut into 1/2-inch strips, then cut into short pieces.

title: donna's best cheese cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream the cheese and sour cream until smooth, add sugar and egg yolks, one at a time. Add lemon and vanilla.
Fold egg whites into cream cheese mixture.

title: italian scrambled eggs
directions: Saute peppers and onion slices in 1/4 cup of butter or margarine in a skillet with medium heat until tender.
Add zucchini, squash and salt.
Cook for two minutes.
While cooking, add scrambled eggs and milk to another pan with 2 tablespoons olive oil on medium heat.
Stir eggs constantly and add vegetables to them as they cook.
When eggs begin to set, add cheese.
Turn heat down and allow cheese to melt over top.
Serves 4 people.

title: iota beta hoppers
directions: Soften ice cream at room temperature or in microwave at 50% power for 1 minute for easier blending.
Place ice cream in blender and add liquors.
Blend at high speed until well blended but slightly thick.
Pour into glasses; sprinkle with cinnamon. Serve immediately.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all the fruits and cherries.
Slice apples in medium size pieces.
Chop the pecans.
Slice the bananas.
Mix all fruits and nuts; slowly add Cool Whip and mix well.
Cool for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta per directions on box.
Drain and set aside to cool.
Chop veggies and set aside.
Mix salad dressing with mayonnaise and season with garlic powder and black pepper to taste.
When pasta is completely cooled, mix in veggies and dressing.
Best if stored overnight to meld seasonings.
Makes enough for a large cookout.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a lightly greased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour glaze over potatoes.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade theraflu
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drink 1 cupful every hour.
Take a nap. Repeat taking 2 aspirin every 4 hours.
If not taking any medication, you can substitute 1 shot booze for the vinegar.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside. Beat egg in large bowl and add onion, crumbs, beef, salt and pepper. Add half the tomato mixture and blend. Pat meat loaf into ball and turn out into a shallow baking pan. Shape into loaf. Pour remaining tomato sauce on top. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, basting occasionally. Serves 8.

title: overnight chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken (other parts of chicken can be used) and salt until tender, about 1 hour.
Let cool.
Remove skin, debone and coarsely chop.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well, then place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine undiluted soup, sour cream, sherry, paprika, mustard, curry powder and mayonnaise; pour 1/2 of soup mixture over broccoli.
Arrange chicken over sauce.
Top with remaining sauce.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before baking at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: fresh tomato basil soup
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan.
Saute onion and garlic about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add basil, honey, bay leaf and tomato paste.
Reduce heat and cook 10 minutes.
Puree in blender; strain.
To puree, add cornstarch and stock.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 10 minutes over low heat.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with julienne tomatoes and basil.
Can be frozen.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shannon's cookies(low-fat and child-approved)
directions: (Low-fat, high fiber, yummy and easy for kids to make!)

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix until fluffy.
Pour into greased, floured Bundt pan.
Preheat oven for 30 minutes at 350°. Bake for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter together, then mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook together broccoli, onion, bouillon cubes, salt and water 25 minutes.
Add cornstarch to milk (mix well).
Add to ingredients; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Serves 4.

title: diet soup
directions: Chop all vegetables into small bits.
Put in pot with tomatoes and add water until food is covered.
Put on medium heat and cook 45 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Fry, drain and crumble sausage.
Slightly beat eggs.
Cube bread in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Combine all and pour in 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Quick, easy and excellent for overnight company.
May also be served for supper.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll up tortillas tightly.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: party punch
directions: Bring to boil sugar and water; set off stove and slowly stir in jello, then frozen lemonade.
After lemonade melts, add pineapple juice and extract.
Add to water; freeze.
When ready to use, thaw six hours and chip into slush; add 7-Up or ginger ale. Makes 60 cups.

title: mom's easy ham sandwiches
directions: Mix together onions, poppy seed, melted butter and mustard.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, cinnamon, apple pie spice and vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) round pans (well-greased).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Combine 1 cup prepared topping; mix with the pie filling mix, pumpkin, milk and spices.
Mix slowly with mixer just until well blended, about 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set, at least 2 hours.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, egg yolks, brown sugar, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Add milk, blending until smooth. Beat
egg whites until foamy and gradually add sugar, beating until
stiff. Fold
into sweet potato mixture.
Pour into pie shells
and sprinkle with additional spices, if desired.
Bake at 400°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 more minutes.
When cool,
garnish
with
whipped cream and orange rind.

title: frozen raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add frozen raspberries; stir until thawed.
Let set until partially congealed.
Add applesauce and lemon juice.
Chill until set.
Blend sour cream, salad dressing and marshmallows.
Spread atop gelatin.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours more or overnight.

title: asparagus and mushroom vinaigrette
directions: In a large skillet, cook asparagus in a small amount of boiling water for 3 minutes or until done; drain. Arrange asparagus and mushrooms in a pyrex dish. In a jar, shake all other ingredients. Pour over asparagus and mushrooms. Cover. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: new years black-eye pea dish
directions: Cook sausage or ground beef in skillet; drain. Add green pepper and onions, cook 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and stir well, add black-eye beas (do not drain). Pour mixture into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 - 25 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over casserole and bake until melted.

title: 6 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: customized tex-mex salsa
directions: In 4 separate bowls put one of the 4 ingredients.
Some Tex-Mex cooks add a little vegetable oil and/or cider vinegar so have a small cruet of each available, also lime wedges.
This is good anyway the user wants to eat it; in a big dish with chips or sprinkled over Tex-Mex food.
Just tell your guests to put the salsa together to please their palates and appetites.

title: crazy crunch popcorn
directions: Mix popcorn, walnuts and almonds together in large pan or cookie sheet.
Cook sugar, butter and Karo syrup, stirring often. Cook until deep caramel color or firm ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn mixture.
Mix well.
Make into balls if desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in the boiling water.
Cool.
Grind the cranberries, apples and the whole orange, including 1/2 of the orange peeling.
Add to the Jell-O mixture.
Chill until set solid and serve.

title: company potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skin until done.
Peel skin from potatoes and slice.
In medium saucepan, combine butter, sour cream and cream of chicken soup, mix until warm.
Combine cheese and melt.
Pour over sliced potatoes, top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cream soup, mayonnaise and eggs together.
Fold in rest of ingredients, except bread crumbs and cheese.
Place in well-greased 9 x 12-inch Pyrex casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Add crumbs and cheese the last 15 minutes or baking time.

title: brazilian pudding
directions: Melt the sugar until brown in a Bundt cake pan; add 4 eggs, condensed milk and milk.
Cover with lid and boil.
Cook in a double boiler pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Refrigerate before serving.
Serves 8 people.

title: soup stuffing
directions: In skillet, brown sausage and cook onion until tender.
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Blend in soup.
Toss lightly with toasted bread cubes.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 1/2 cups stuffing or enough for a 5 or 6 pound bird.

title: meatball stew
directions: Make hamburger into small meatballs and roll in flour.
Brown in oil; drain.
Combine meatballs, carrots, potatoes, onions, bouillon, soup and salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: cocoa kiss cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar together until creamy.
Beat in vanilla and egg.
Combine the flour and baking soda.
Beat into butter mixture.
Stir in the coconut and white chocolate.
Form a dough.

title: strawberry daiquiri pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in daiquiri mix, rum and food coloring, if desired.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour into prepared crust.
Chill or freeze 4 hours or until firm. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate or freeze leftovers.

title: $100.00 cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in layer or loaf pans. Grease pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: super fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Then boil slowly, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla until chocolate is melted.
Turn into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and cool.

title: farmhouse stew
directions: Crumble beef in 3-quart microwave dish.
Add potato, cabbage, onion and celery.
Cook on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients; cover and microwave 18 to 24 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: crisp oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine potato flakes, seasoned salt, paprika, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir in butter; mix well.
In medium bowl, beat water and egg until well combined. Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture; coat all sides with potato flake mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up, in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: lisa's old-fashioned dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the 1/2 cup chicken broth and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out on a floured surface and form into a ball.
Roll dough to a 1/16-inch thickness and cut into diamonds or whatever shape you prefer.
Drop dumplings into boiling broth or soup.
Cover and cook for about 15 minutes or until dumplings are tender.
We use this in chicken and dumplings.

title: super bowl cake
directions: In a clear, large bowl, layer half of cake pieces and top with half of the pudding.
Spread evenly across cake pieces.
Add half of Cool Whip and half of chocolate.
Repeat layering, ending with chocolate.
Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
To serve, scoop out over serving plates.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 14-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spread coconut and pecans on bottom.
Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Melt butter or oleo.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Spread over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cake will crack down the middle hence its name.
Serves 36.

title: eggplant-onion casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, cut into small pieces, cover with water and salt and pepper.
Boil until tender.
Drain.
Add cheese, egg, onion and milk.
Put into buttered casserole dish, top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in flour, sugars and then melted oleo.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping. Yields 8 servings.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown chops in hot fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn chops once during baking.
Makes 8 servings.

title: yummy yams
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans in a large mixing bowl, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole; arrange nuts around edge of dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken with honey-mustard glaze
directions: In large jar or blender, combine all ingredients except chicken to blend.
Pour this mixture over chicken in a shallow dish. Cover and marinate 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Drain chicken, reserve marinade.
Grill chicken over medium coals for 45 to 50 minutes, brushing with marinade and turning frequently.
Just before serving, brush with Honey-Mustard Glaze.
Makes 6 servings.

title: williamsburg pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix the ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until the middle of the pie is set.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a punch bowl, layer crumbled cake first, then add a layer of pineapple, vanilla pudding, coconut, pecans, Cool Whip then pie filling.
Continue until punch bowl is layered to top.
Top with whipped cream and decorate with cherries and pecans.

title: easy chicken divine
directions: Place cooked broccoli in buttered casserole dish (about an 8 x 12-inch pan).
Place chicken on broccoli.
Mix soup, curry powder, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
This can be prepared ahead of time (night before) or prepared without crumbs and placed in freezer for later use, adding crumbs before cooking.

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Put vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Salt and pepper meat, then put in pot over vegetables.
Add liquid.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or cook on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: pound cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Blend flour into butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Refrigerate dough until thoroughly chilled.
Form small balls about the size of a quarter and press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Using thumb, press indentation in top of each cookie and fill with small amount of strawberry jam. If you prefer, press a pecan half on top of cookies.
Bake 12 minutes at 300° or until lightly browned.
Cool several minutes, then slide cookies off pan, using a spatula.
Makes about 6 to 7 dozen cookies.
Keep stored in an airtight container for a crisp, delightful treat.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Blend on low speed until moistened. Beat on high speed for 2 minutes. Pour into 2 (9-inch) round, greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans to wire racks to cool completely.

title: hearty beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef in stockpot with a little oil or cooking spray.
Add soup mix and tabasco, stirring to evenly distribute. Add water, tomato sauce, bay leaf and vegetables. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover & simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in pepper & serve piping hot!

title: dracula's delight
directions: Mix apple juice, cranberry juice, lemon juice, sliced lemon and pineapple bits in a large container.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Before serving, add ginger ale and pour into a punch bowl with ice.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: donna's winter barley soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat (add oil if using sirloin cubes). Drain oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Stir in all except frozen vegetables.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add frozen vegetables and cook 10 minutes.
You may use fresh vegetables; just cook until tender.

title: peanut butter pie(low-fat)
directions: Mix together graham crackers and margarine and press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix all remaining ingredients together; pour in pie crust and freeze.
Exchanges: 1/2 bread; 1 1/2 fat; 1 protein; 1/2 fruit; 1/2 milk; 50 optional calories.

title: scrumptious chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts, sesame seed and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Blend well and set aside.

title: spicy black bean and corn salad
directions: Combine beans, cheese, corn, green onions, celery and red pepper in large bowl.
Combine picante sauce, oil, lemon juice, cumin and garlic; mix well.
Toss with bean mixture.
Chill.
May serve with additional picante sauce, if desired.
Makes 8 servings or about 5 cups of salad.
Preparation Time:
30 minutes.

title: choco-dot pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, spices and sugar.
Set aside.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix together and form into small balls.
Refrigerate until cold.
Melt 24 ounces of semi-sweet chocolate chips and 1/2 bar of paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Put on wax paper.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese, blending in sugar with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, and continue to blend. Add flavorings and flour and beat until smooth.
Don't overbeat. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven 1 1/2 hours until cake is golden.

title: apple pie ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Finish filling the container to the fill line with milk, if needed.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: red pork chops
directions: Place chops in a small amount oil and brown. Remove from pan. Saute onions and bell pepper. Add 2 cans of stewed tomatoes. Be sure to mash any large pieces. Stir well.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla and mix.
Add oatmeal and mix.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg and then add to mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Place 1 1/2-inch balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 12 to 13 minutes for crispy cookies.

title: hamburger salad
directions: Melt oleo.
Add meat and onions.
Brown.
Add rest of ingredients plus salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until carrots are done.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: Arrange chicken in casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: rhubarb brown betty
directions: Mix bread and rhubarb, add butter, hot water, sugar, salt and cinnamon in order.
Bake 1/2 hour with cover and 1/2 hour without cover.

title: 4 layer surprise
directions: Blend flour, softened butter and pecans.
Spread into 11 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 375° until light brown (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip and powdered sugar into cream cheese.
Spread on cool crust.
Mix pudding and 3 cups milk until set; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Chill.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly on bottom of a 9 x 11 casserole dish. Spread chili on top of cream cheese. Place in oven and broil at 400 until mixture begins to bubble. When bubbling, remove from oven and sprinkle with cheddar cheese. Place back in oven until cheese has melted. Serve with Tortilla chips.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together everything but onions and half of the cheese. Put into a casserole or baking pan.
Sprinkle with some of the cheese and top with onions.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bean and sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion, carrots, celery and garlic in oil until tender. Remove vegetables from pan.
Brown sausage in same skillet. Combine vegetables, sausage, tomato sauce, beans, thyme and salt. Pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: In large bowl, add beaten eggs to all ingredients except sour cream, add this last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream
directions: Heat milk.
Put together cornstarch and salt with 2 cups milk. Add to hot milk; stir until slightly thick, but do not boil! Pour hot milk over the beaten eggs and sugar; cool.
When ready to freeze, add cream and vanilla.
Pour into freezer through a sieve. Add more milk if it isn't 3/4 full.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: day'o banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease two loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch, with shortening.
Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pans.

title: leonard jefferies' buckwheat cakes(age 96)
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients well.
Add buttermilk and flour.
Beat until well mixed.
Bake on hot greased griddle.
Easy, quick and good.

title: diabetic chip cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter, Sweet *10, vanilla and egg.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add chocolate pieces.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: heavenly hash (candy)
directions: Cook until soft ball stage, when you drop a couple of drops in cold water.
Add nuts and beat for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: light cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add milk and eggs.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and 1/4 cup cooking oil in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of oil mixture in batter; leave rest in pan.
Pour batter in pan and use a spoon to spoon excess oil on top of batter.
This forms a thick crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage with salt and butter in microwave oven for 6 minutes in a covered dish.
Remove and serve.

title: monkey cake
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters in a large bowl.
Mix cinnamon, 2/3 cup sugar, nuts and/or raisins with biscuits.
Pour into greased tube pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven. Serve warm or cold.

title: bruschetta with chicken
directions: Mix ricotta with salt, pepper and parsley; set aside. Mix together chicken, tomatoes, garlic, olive oil and basil; season to taste with salt and pepper; set aside. Slice bread into 12 slices. Broil until lightly toasted, turning once. Spread ricotta mixture on bread, top with tomato mixture and balsamic vinegar (if using). Serve immediately.

title: cream cheese braids
directions: Heat sour cream over low heat; stir in sugar, salt and butter. Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water in large mixing bowl, stirring until yeast dissolves.
Add sour cream mixture, eggs and flour; mix well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken with crab sauce fettucini
directions: Skin, wash and dry the chicken breasts.
Coat thoroughly with black pepper, a little salt and lemon pepper.
Rub with enough mayonnaise on each to glaze with thin coating.
Place (bone side down) in lightly oiled (1 teaspoon olive oil), big black iron skillet.
Set oven to 400° and bake until golden brown and tender, about 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush half of the cookies into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar together.
Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Combine pudding with cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour on top of cookie layer.
Crush rest of cookies and sprinkle on top.

title: stove-top carob cookies
directions: Combine sugar, carob
and milk in saucepan and boil hard for 1 minute.
Stirring constantly, fold in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop from a spoon onto waxed paper and let harden. Store in airtight container.

title: ernie's creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except last 2 and bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend butter with flour (I melt in microwave) and add to corn.
Mix well and remove from heat.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix nuts, candy and crumbs.
Melt margarine and marshmallows. Mix well.
Shape into logs and roll in confectioners sugar.
Chill and slice.

title: orange banana nut bread
directions: Beat sugar, butter and egg until smooth.
Add bananas, orange peel and milk.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Beat just until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Let cool 10 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Blend with a hand mixer until well mixed.
Add brandy or bourbon, if desired.

title: stroganoff
directions: On medium heat, brown butter in skillet.
Add steak and onions, stirring to cook evenly.
Add mushrooms; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Slowly add cream and stir. Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: peach-plum jam
directions: Boil rapidly until thick.
Stir, as will burn.
Pour into jars and seal.
It is go good!!

title: the broccoli and everything salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chopped broccoli, raisins, cooked diced bacon, and raw chopped onions.
Add the dressing to combined ingredients and stir to coat evenly.
Ready to eat or chill.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and add 1 quart of water.
Chill and serve.

title: french pancake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
(If possible, make the night before and refrigerate.)
Place Crisco oil in frying pan.
Heat until very hot.
Pour batter to cover frying pan, but not thick, they should be very thin, like crepes, 1 pancake at a time.
Edges will curl and brown.
Flip pancake; cook until brown, only a few seconds.
Serve with syrup.

title: 100 year old egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Beat eggs, sugar and oleo, add flour to mixture, add milk and mix well. Place in unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes or until custard doesn't shake in center.

title: best peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Beat in eggs, peanut butter.
Blend in flour, salt, and soda.
Add vanilla.
Roll dough into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown on edges. Makes 120 cookies.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Take College Avenue to Taco Bell.
Go to drive up window; order Mexican Pizza.
Pay at window.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Heat 1 cup salted water to boiling, add broccoli or cauliflower, cover, bring to a boil and cook until almost tender (about 5 minutes). Drain thoroughly.
Mix cooked vegetables with onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over ingredients in pie plate.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.
Let stand before cutting.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tostones
directions: Peel plantain and cut into diagonal 3/4-inch thick slices. Deep fry in hot oil at 375° until tender, but hot crusty (1 to 2 minutes).
Drain on paper towel.
Cover with wax paper and press down on each plantain with palm of hand to flatten.
Deep fry again until crusty and golden on both sides.
Drain.
Season lightly with Adobo and serve hot.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer lettuce, green peppers, onions, celery and green peas.
Spread mayonnaise over top of the vegetable layers and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of mayonnaise.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: old-fashioned tea cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well. Add flour, baking powder and soda, 1 cup at a time, alternately with buttermilk, until enough flour.
Make dough like cookie dough.
Put in bowl and work flour in.
Make 6 balls of dough. Put in pan.
Cook at 375° until lightly brown, around 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package. Drain well. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cooked broccoli in a casserole dish. Cover with grated cheese or cracker crumbs. (I use both and sometimes add French fried onions). Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: delicious apple cake
directions: Beat well the oil and eggs.
Add vanilla, sugar, flour, soda, salt,
cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix apples, 1/4 cup flour, nuts
and coconut
and
fold	into batter.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 70 minutes, or bake
in
x
13-inch
cake pan for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and put into casserole dish. In a microwave safe bowl, add cheese whiz and butter, stirring after every minute until melted. Pour over vegetables and top with crumbled Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: curry-crusted bananas
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Half the bananas lengthwise, then crosswise.
In a bowl, mix the melted butter and the curry powder. Dip the bananas in butter mixture.
Roll in the cornflakes until completely coated and sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Place the bananas in a greased baking dish and bake for 10 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle bacon pieces and cheese in bottom of pie shell. Beat eggs slightly, add whipping cream.
Mix gently, mixture will thicken slightly.
Pour over cheese and bacon in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes then at 300° for 30 minutes.
This is good served with fruit salad and muffins.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs and fruit cocktail juice.
Add flour, baking soda and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add fruit cocktail.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 oblong pan.
Sprinkle dark brown sugar and nuts over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool cake 5 minutes and then make icing.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Combine all ingredients (except Velveeta) in chicken broth in large casserole dish.
Stir together.
Cut Velveeta up on top and cook in oven about 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves about 8.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Thaw sugar cookie dough.
Press dough into pizza pan.
Cook until golden brown.
Cool.	Mix cream cheese, half of sugar, orange peel, milk, and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Layer with a variety of fruits.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Put vanilla wafers in bottom of liners in muffin pan. Beat ingredients together with mixer until light and fluffy.
Pour into liners about 1/2 to 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until well set. Let cool for 15 minutes.
Add topping and refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts covered in water (salt and pepper to taste) for about 30 minutes or until tender.
Mix up Stove Top dressing mix as directed on package.
Drain chicken breasts and save about 1 cup broth.
Cut up or break chicken breasts in small pieces.
Put about 1/2 of chicken pieces into 2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Put rest of chicken in with Stove Top mix.
Stir together and put over chicken pieces.
Mix up about 3/4 cup broth with soup and pour over chicken and stuffing mixture.
Using a spoon, move dressing around so soup will go down into dressing.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown on edges.

title: ritz cracker mock apple pie
directions: Roll out bottom crust of pastry; put in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 18 Ritz crackers, coarsely crushed, in pastry lined pan.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan; boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and lemon rind; cool.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot generously with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover with top crust.
Trim and flute edges together.
Cut slits in top crust to let steam out.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is crisp.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: famous cookie recipe
directions: Combine ingredients; beat well. Stir in 24 ounces chocolate chips. Add about 6 cups all-purpose flour. Spoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 11 to 12 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, salt, lard and sugar.
Heat
in saucepan.
Cool.
Stir in yeast mixture. Add flour.
Mix well.
Let rise, covered, 15 minutes (no need to knead).
Place
balls
in muffin pan, cloverleaf style. Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.

title: orange-nut muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
In separate bowl, mix soda and sour cream.
Add eggs and sour cream mixture to butter/egg mixture. Fold in flour, nuts, orange and vanilla.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tops are lightly brown.
(This batter may be refrigerated overnight.)

title: spinach balls
directions: *Use 6 eggs instead of these 2 ingredients.

title: yankee succotash
directions: Drain vegetables and put in saucepan with butter, pepper and milk.
Bring to a slow simmer for approximately 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to vegetables.
Simmer slowly until thickened, stirring frequently.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs; add melted butter, sugar and salt.
Add soda to buttermilk; add egg mixture and then flour.

title: hollandaise sauce(microwave)
directions: Place butter in a 2 cup measuring cup.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir in lemon juice, egg yolks, cream, mustard, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Microwave on High 1 minute, stirring every 15 seconds.
Beat with a wire whisk until smooth.
Sauce can be reheated on High for 1 minute.
Makes 2/3 cup.

title: peanut butter roast
directions: For each cup of cake flour called for, place 2 tablespoons cornstarch in a one-cup measure.
Then fill to the top with all-purpose flour.

title: green grape salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
(Can use more cream cheese and less mayonnaise if preferred.)

title: chocolate mayo cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with wax paper.
Melt butter and chocolate chips; set aside. In a bowl or food processor, pour remaining ingredients.
Now, add chocolate mixture.
Mix on high until batter is smooth.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool until pan can be touched before removing.
Frost with Satiny Beige Frosting.

title: patchwork casserole
directions: Cook ground beef.
Add green pepper and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Spoon 1/2 of meat mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan and top with 1/2 of cheese.
Spoon remaining mixture over cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut remaining cheese and top casserole.

title: old fashioned lemonade
directions: Combine lemon juice and sugar in a large pitcher; stir until sugar dissolves. Add water and lemon slices.
Stir well and chill. Serve over ice with lemon slices.

title: mango-strawberry cooler
directions: Toss first five ingredients to mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix in butter and milk.
Dump out on floured board.
Knead 2 to 3 times.
Rol out into 14 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spread 2/3 of the fruit mix evenly over dough.
Roll the dough up like a jelly roll.
Cut into seven even portions. Distribute in 9-inch cake pan lined with parchment.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place remaining fruit mix in small saucepan. Cook on medium heat until thick.

title: chicken pie
directions: In a large saucepan, heat soup, vegetables, broth, seasoning and parsley until bubbly.
Fold in chicken.
Spoon hot mixture into 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with roll dough.
Bake in 375° oven 9 to 12 minutes until top is lightly brown.

title: white chili
directions: Simmer slowly for 1 to 2 hours.

title: steph's gourmet pasta
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
While pasta is cooking, in a large frying pan, warm olive oil (medium heat), toss in bread crumbs; brown (about 3 minutes).
Chop Prosciutto.
Drain pasta and toss all together.
Enjoy.

title: turnips(usa)
directions: Peel and slice turnips.
Place turnips, sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until turnips are tender and begin to turn pink or red.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cover with catsup.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and salt, slowly beating all the time.
Fold in chocolate chips, pecans and vanilla.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets covered with foil.
Place cookies in preheated oven.
Close door and turn off oven.
Leave cookies in oven for 8 hours or overnight.
Peel carefully from foil when cookies are done.
Store in airtight container.
May use food coloring for decorative purposes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: grandma's rum cake
directions: Grease 12-cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pan. In a large bowl, mix well the cake and pudding mix.
Add eggs, milk, rum and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over chopped nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, test with a toothpick.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan onto serving dish and prick top and sides with a fork.

title: macaroni-shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse frozen peas under running cold water to separate; drain.
Mix macaroni, peas and remaining ingredients except lettuce and bacon.
Refrigerate until chilled, at least 4 hours.
Just before serving, toss macaroni mixture with lettuce and bacon.
Makes 6 servings, 455 calories per serving.

title: green pepper sandwiches
directions: Mix peppers, onion, cream cheese and seasonings with enough mayonnaise to make spreadable.
Let mixture set for 30 minutes before making sandwiches.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Heat margarine and oil in oblong 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish in a 400° oven until margarine is melted.
Place chicken in dish, turning to coat with margarine mixture.
Arrange chicken, sprinkled with garlic salt.
Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Mix soup, mushrooms (with liquid), water, Worcestershire sauce and thyme.
Rinse broccoli under running cold water to separate; drain.
Remove chicken from oven; drain fat from dish.
Arrange broccoli along sides of chicken; sprinkle with salt.
Spoon soup mixture over broccoli.
Cook, uncovered, until chicken is done and broccoli is tender, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with paprika.

title: la madeline tomato soup
directions: Combine tomatoes and juice in a large saucepan on medium heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Combine tomato and basil mixture in a blender or processor; do in small batches until smooth.
Return to saucepan on low heat.
Stir in cream and butter.
Heat thoroughly. Garnish with Parmesan cheese and basil.

title: polish delight
directions: Heat oil, add meat.
Saute over medium heat until brown, about 10 minutes.
Stir in soups and soup mix; spoon into 13 x 9-inch pan, or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° covered until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Add water if needed.
Add noodles and sauerkraut, mix all ingredients together.
Cover and bake another 30 minutes (about).

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Beat eggs in medium bowl until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and strawberries.
In large bowl, blend sifted flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add strawberry mixture and mix until well blended. Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing.

title: tomato, avocado and bibb lettuce salad(serves 4)
directions: Make dressing according to package directions.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream butter well and add sugar.
Cream until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to butter and sugar mixture, alternating with milk.
Mix well.
Add coloring and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: "frannie bell's" italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco. Add egg yolks. Add flour, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Beat egg whites stiff, then fold in coconut. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: low-fat moist chocolate cupcakes(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 16 to 18 minutes.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground turkey.
Add garlic salt, Prego and water.
Bring to boil and remove from heat.
In 9 x 13-inch glass dish, layer 1/3 of sauce, 1/2 of uncooked lasagna noodles, 1/2 of Ricotta cheese and 1/2 of Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Uncover; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: okra and tomatoes(microwave)
directions: In a 3-quart casserole dish, stir in ingredients. Cover and cook on High 1 hour.
Salt and pepper. Stir occasionally.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: In a saucepan, melt morsels, margarine, crumbs and nuts. Press 1/2 mixture firmly into buttered baking pan.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk, egg and vanilla.
Pour into pan.
Top remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Chill before cutting bars.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until boils, stirring occasionally. Add 1-inch of Velveeta cheese.
Stir until dissolved.
In the meantime, cook the macaroni as directed on package.
Combine cooked macaroni and cheese mixture in a casserole dish.
Add more sliced Velveeta cheese to your liking.
Bake 15 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: corn-kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Stir into this mixture, eggs, nuts and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda.
Add this to the creamed mixture alternately with milk and honey.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Frost or glaze as desired.

title: camper's delight
directions: You will need aluminum foil.

title: naomi's chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Mix altogether and cook until form a very soft ball.
Remove from fire.
Add heaping tablespoon of oleo or butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until stiff enough for spreading.
Can also add nuts and pour into dish and cut into squares for chocolate fudge candy.

title: cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix all together. Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll ball in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoon cinnamon. Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until light brown, but still soft, about 10 minutes.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Crush cardamom seeds and tie in cheesecloth with cloves and broken cinnamon stick.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add spices and bring slowly to boil.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pineapple, marshmallows, bananas and nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.
In saucepan, cook sugar, pineapple juice, egg, flour and butter.
Add cheese and Dream Whip.
Spread on Jell-O.
Chill.

title: round steak with rich gravy
directions: Sprinkle one side of meat with half the flour; pound in.
Turn meat and pound in remaining flour.
Cut meat into 6 to 8 serving pieces.

title: snowballs
directions: Add sugar to cooked rice.
Add egg yolks to the cooked rice. Form rice (after cooled) into round balls.
Place a marshmallow in center of a pineapple ring.
Place rice ball on top of the marshmallow.
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and spread over the rice ball.
Brown in oven until meringue is brown.
Makes 6.

title: crab alfredo
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Set aside. Saute mushrooms in garlic and 1 tablespoon margarine.
Add margarine and cream to hot noodles and toss.
Add Parmesan cheese, mushrooms and crab.
Toss again.

title: guacamole
directions: Use the basic ingredients plus any or all of the optional ingredients.
Blend in a blender or mash well with a fork until smooth.
Guacamole can be used as a dip or spread for corn chips, crackers or bread or as a dressing or main ingredient in salad. Makes 2 to 2 1/2 cups.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix
like
pie dough, gradually adding 1/2 cup of milk. Roll and
cut
into
3-inch
squares.
Quarter apples.
Place brown sugar
in
center of apples and sprinkle with cinnamon. Make syrup and bring to a boil (1 cup brown sugar, 1 cup water and 2 tablespoons margarine).
Pour over dumplings and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and juice until smooth. Fold in fluff and mix well. This is wonderful with fresh fruit; strawberries, grapes, pineapple, kiwi, bananas, etc.

title: snowballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Will appear crumbly.
Compress into small (walnut size) balls.
Bake at 350° on ungreased sheets for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar immediately!

title: crazy cake
directions: 1. Pour last four ingredients into dry mix and stir all together. DO NOT BEAT !
2. Bake in a 9x13x2 pan at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit, bring to boil.
Dissolve Jello in juice.
Add water to make 2 1/2 cups of liquid.
Cool, add fruits & nuts and cokes. Chill.

title: hot pecan dip
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, milk and sour cream until smooth. Add green chilies, onion and salt to mixture.
Shred the jar of dried beef.
Fold dried beef into mixture.
Turn mixture into an 8-inch baking dish.
In small skillet melt butter and brown pecans. Spread pecans over mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: easy peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark in low oven (about 225°).
Stir in peanuts. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let set.
White almond bark and 3 tablespoons cocoa may be used.

title: date nut rolls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix together crumbs with nuts, dates, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Mix together very well.
Make into the shape of logs.
Wrap in wax paper.
Makes approximately 3 rolls.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice amount needed when ready to serve.

title: taco pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls in pie dish to form crust.
Brown meat and onion; drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning and water; simmer for 5 minutes.
Spread meat mixture over dough; sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Add chips.
Serves 6.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar-free banana or peach pudding
directions: In glass dish, place wafers on bottom.
Then layer with fruit and pudding.
Add second layer of wafers and fruit and pudding if desired.
Top with prepared whipped topping.

title: far east salad
directions: Combine vinegar, soy sauce and ground ginger.
Add chicken and marinate for 15 to 30 minutes.
In salad bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Just before serving, remove chicken from marinade; reserve.
Pour marinade into cabbage mixture; toss and top with chicken.

title: spinach casserole(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions omitting salt. Combine sour cream, onion soup and melted butter.
Drain spinach well and add to sour cream mixture.
Place in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cook onions until clear, remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, curry powder and pepper.
Slowly stir in 1 cup of water in skillet of flour mixture, then add the milk until you make a sauce.
Put cut up chicken and broccoli together in casserole dish, then mix the Cheddar cheese and sauce with the broccoli and chicken.
Mix well, then top with the Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake in the oven for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate strawberry shortcake
directions: Reserve 6 strawberries. Slice remaining berries into bowl. Gently stir in 1/4 cup sugar; set aside.
Preheat oven to 450°. Grease an 8-inch round cake pan.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, cocoa, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
In separate bowl, stir together milk and egg. Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spread dough in prepared pan, building up edges slightly. Bake in a 450° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Place on serving plate.

title: lemon curd filling
directions: In a small saucepan stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in the mandarin peel, lemon juice and water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.

title: crazy-8 carob cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in Bundt pan 35 to 45 minutes, cupcakes 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch sheet cake pan 30 minutes, or half recipe for 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in cherries; add sifted ingredients, nut meats, dates and chopped cherries.
Mix well.
Crush flakes slightly. Roll teaspoon of dough in crumbs, place on greased cookie sheet. Press 1/4 cherry into each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: yankee beef vegetables
directions: Brown ground beef; add vegetables, setting aside enclosed topping packet.
Combine 1/4 cup water, bouillon cube, Worcestershire sauce and cornstarch; add to skillet containing ground beef and vegetables.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. sprinkle with topping.
Makes 2 to 3 main dish servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, milk, melted butter and flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Continue beating until very light.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: german stollen
directions: Combine yeast and flour; add to milk.
Let rise until light. Add remaining ingredients.
Knead.
Let rise until very light.

title: broken glass cake
directions: Prepare the jello according to directions (assorted colors and flavors).
Pour into 3 shallow pans and keep in refrigerator overnight.
Mix 1 3/4 cups crumbs with 1/2 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Use to line bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add hot juice and heat until gelatine is dissolved.
Cool.
Whip packaged topping with vanilla, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 cup milk.
Fold unflavored gelatin into this mixture.
Cut fruit jello into small cubes and fold into topping mixture.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and Italian mix together.
Roll into ball.
Roll ball in ground nuts.
To make a dip instead of a ball, add enough milk to the cheese, margarine and Italian mix to dipping consistency and omit nuts.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cut each strip of bacon into thirds. Wrap 6 to 8 beans with bacon. Secure with a toothpick. Sprinkle with garlic salt. In a small pan, melt margarine. Add brown sugar. Cook 1 minute or until sugar melts. Pour over beans. Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes or until bacon is brown.

title: hungarian chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper and place in a plastic bag. Shake chicken a few pieces at a time in flour mixture.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in large skillet.
Saute onion until tender. Remove from pan and set aside.
In same skillet, melt remaining butter and brown chicken on all sides.
Combine tomato juice, paprika, sugar and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Add bay leaf, broth and reserved onion.
Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to a platter; keep warm.
Reduce heat to low.
Remove bay leaf and stir in sour cream.
Heat through 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken and noodles.
Serves 6.

title: st. louis barbecue shrimp
directions: Mix sauce, seasoning and pepper, dash of hot sauce, thyme and oil in a bowl until well blended.
Add shrimp, turning to coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Lift shrimp from marinade and place on skewers.
Place on greased grill 6-inches above solid bed of low glowing coals or place on a rimmed baking sheet and broil 6-inches from heat.
Cook, basting frequently and turn once, until shrimp turns pink, approximately 4 minutes per side.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: frosty hermits
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat until light.
Alternately add flour mixture and sour cream, beating until blended.
Add fruit, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° up to 10 minutes.
Frost tops while hot with glaze.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: rocky road clusters
directions: Combine morsels and sweetened condensed milk in large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High (100%) power for 1 minute. Stir until smooth.
If necessary, microwave for 20 to 30 seconds longer to complete melting.
Stir in marshmallows, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by heaping tablespoon into mounds on wax paper. Chill until firm.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix sour cream with Jell-O.
Add Cool Whip and blend.
Add well drained fruit and marshmallow.
Stir to mix.
Add chopped nuts on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Mix salt, cocoa and sugar.
Add milk and butter; bring to boil.
Continue boiling until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla when just warm.
Beat until creamy.

title: easy asian beef and noodles
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut steak diagonally across grain into thin slices.
Heat 1/2 teaspoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add steak and onions; stir-fry 1 minute. Remove steak mixture from skillet; keep warm.
Heat remaining 1/2 teaspoon oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add slaw; stir-fry 30 seconds.
Remove slaw from skillet; keep warm.
Remove noodles from package; reserve 1 season packet for another use.
Add water and remaining seasoning packet to skillet; bring to a boil.
Break noodles in half; add noodles to water mixture.
Cook noodles 2 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed, stirring frequently.
Stir in steak mixture, slaw and soy sauce; cook until thoroughly heated.
Makes 2 servings (2 cup size). Points: 10.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Add flour and cayenne and mix well. Add egg, olives and water chestnuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: mincemeat fruit cake
directions: Add raisins, mincemeat, nuts, sugar, butter, vanilla and egg yolks in bowl.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Sift again and fold into mincemeat mixture.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Can be eaten the same day.
It can also be baked and frozen until Christmastime.

title: raspberry vinegar
directions: Combine vinegar and 1 cup berries in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 2 minutes.
Stir in honey and remove from heat.
Pour berry mixture through a fine mesh strainer into a large measuring cup.
Don't press down on berries.
Discard the berries.

title: grits bread(cream of wheat bread)
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add milk, oil and eggs.
Stir gently.
Pour into hot, greased skillet and bake at 425° until done.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and shortening; stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Will keep as long as 5 to 6 weeks.
When ready to bake, spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yield: about 5 1/2 dozen.
tags: box wheat bran flakes cereal with raisins

title: cranberry salad
