directions: Put cranberries, water and salt on stove.
When it starts to boil, put in soda and cook for 10 minutes.
Add sugar and jello; stir until dissolved.
Add marshmallows while hot.
Cool; add apples, celery and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: fig-strawberry preserves(tastes like strawberry preserves)
directions: Mash figs thoroughly.
Mix jello, sugar and figs.
Stir until the sugar dissolves.
Heat.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Place in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop pepper, onion and stems finely.
Saute in butter until tender.
Fill mushroom caps, then sprinkle with cheese.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry and drain the hamburger, onions and chilies. Add soup, sour cream and mix well. Layer Dorito chips, meat mixture and shredded cheese. Cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage ring
directions: Mix all ingredients and press in ring mold to shape.
Bake on a pie plate or in pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve on platter with broiled peaches around mold and scrambled eggs in the center of the ring.

title: chilaquiles(mexican lasagna)
directions: In large skillet saute the onions and garlic in oil until tender, 2 to 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add the carrots and cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in the beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, chilies and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until the mixture thickens slightly, about 5 minutes.
Coat an 8-inch casserole with nonstick spray.
Place one tortilla on the bottom of the casserole. Top with a third of the vegetable mixture and cheese.
Repeat layering twice more and end with the cheese.
Bake at 400° until hot and the cheese melts, 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4:
302 calories and 8.2 g fat per serving.

title: white nut bread
directions: Sift together in mixing bowl flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Combine eggs and milk; add to dry ingredients until moistened.

title: ale 8 one cake
directions: Put all ingredients except egg whites into large mixing bowl and beat 2 minutes.
Fold beaten egg whites into batter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Add oil, orange juice with rind and beaten egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan or paper-lined muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together brown sugar, lard, and egg. Stir in applesauce.
Sift and stir in dry ingredients.
Add raisins.
Drop teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10-12 minutes.

title: quick skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet (electric).
Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, until macaroni is done, about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally while cooking.

title: mexican hot dip
directions: Combine soup and taco sauce.
Layer over this onion and olives.
Spread cheese over top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Serve with taco chips, etc.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, onions and salt pork in enough water to cover. Cook until tender, 30 minutes.
Drain clams, reserving clam juice. Add clams and about half of clam juice to make a soup consistency.
The more juice, the more clam flavor.
Add half and half or tomato juice.
Season to taste.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in salted water until tender.
Drain. Cook until thickened evaporated milk, whole milk, butter and flour.
Stir in Cheddar cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place squash and onion in a casserole and cover with sauce.
Pour enough dressing on top of casserole to cover and dot with butter.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, until browned.

title: simple baked pork chops
directions: Place chops in shallow, greased baking dish.
Spread with mustard.
Sprinkle with celery, brown sugar and seasonings.
Pour tomato sauce and water over chops.
Cover baking dish and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/4 hours or until chops are tender. Serves 4.

title: spaghetti with yoghurt and garlic
directions: Saute the garlic slivers in the oil until light brown.
Stir in the yogurt, parsley and seasoning.
Remove from the fire; pour over the boiled spaghetti and serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: apple spritzer punch
directions: In a large container, stir together all ingredients. Carefully pour into punch bowl.
Add maraschino cherries.
Wrap vines around base of punch bowl for presentation.

title: spicy vegetable couscous
directions: Saute vegetables (and tofu, if desired) over medium heat until just tender.
Add chickpeas and spices, except for parsley.

title: squirrel dumplings
directions: Put squirrel in pot of hot water.
Boil about 1 1/2 hours or until fork goes through easily.
Mix flour and grease in a bowl. Put it on a surface that is floured.
Roll around until it is not sticky.
Pinch off into small balls.
Put them in the pot. Sprinkle salt and pepper into squirrel and dumplings.
Stir often. Cook until dumplings are done.

title: sweet red bean dessert sauce
directions: Mix bean paste and Mandarin Marmalade.
Stir in the liqueur. Fold into whipped topping, chill.
Serve over ice cream or pound cake.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; do not overcook.
Chop all vegetables. Combine drained spaghetti and chopped vegetables in a large bowl. Pour dressing and tomato sauce into bowl.
Add seasoning; mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries, stirring until thawed.
Add pineapple.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish and let set.
Gradually add a little milk or cream to cream cheese until consistency of whipped cream.
Add nuts.
When jello is thoroughly set, spread cream cheese and nuts over top.
Cover dish with foil to keep cheese moist.

title: fruit bars
directions: Spread nuts in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour batter made from margarine, brown sugar, eggs and flour, over nuts.
Sprinkle the candied pineapple and candied cherries on top of batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 275°.

title: reubens appetizers
directions: Mix together.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven until hot.
Uncover to brown.
Serve with cocktail rye bread.

title: coconut bars(these taste just like a mounds bar!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until firm and cold.
Shape into small bars and place on a cookie sheet.
Freeze. Melt chocolate and paraffin.
Dip bars in chocolate and place on waxed paper.
Use toothpick to dip them.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix with mixer and bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt shortening.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll into sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Alternate layers of asparagus, soup and sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Pour milk over other ingredients.
Spread buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: flo's cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage, then mash.
Saute onions and celery in oleo. Combine all ingredients and put into greased casserole dish.
Add extra cheese or bread crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour, 1/2 cup buttermilk, salt and flavoring.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 2 minutes after each egg.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour to batter.
Mix 1/2 teaspoon of soda in remaining buttermilk and add it to flour mix.
Beat 2 minutes. Pour into tube pan that has been greased with vegetable oil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal-raisin drop cookies
directions: Boil raisins for 5 minutes in enough water to make 6 tablespoons when done.
Beat shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla together until creamy.
Add raisins and 6 tablespoons juice.
Stir in the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and oatmeal.
Bake at 375° or 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: chocolate topping
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in saucepan; blend in evaporated milk. Add butter or margarine and salt.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture just begins to boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla. Serve warm over ice cream or other desserts.
Makes about 2 cups sauce.
Refrigerate leftovers for another day.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread in greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: country fried chicken in gravy
directions: Season and flour chicken.
Heat Crisco in a large pan.
When hot, add chicken.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Remove from pan. Remove all Crisco from pan, except about 1 tablespoon.
Put 3 teaspoons of flour in pan.
Brown the flour.
Pour 1 cup of water in pan.
Stir until thick.
Put chicken back in pan and cover. Leave in pan until ready to serve.

title: shish kebab(warning, this dish need minimum one hour marination time.)
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients together in a nonmetal bowl and then add the cubed meat and mix well.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and reserve in cool to cold place.

title: banana fruit cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening, then eggs, until creamy.
Add vanilla and sour milk.
Sift in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add bananas, raisins, nuts and candied fruit.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Split hot dogs in half.
Brown hot dogs in butter or salad oil.
Combine remaining ingredients to make the barbecue sauce. Heat sauce and add browned hot dogs.
Best served hot.

title: one minute fudge frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Add other ingredients; boil for 1 minute.
Set off heat and beat until spreading consistency.

title: sweet potato and couscous casserole
directions: In medium size bowl, combine couscous, boiling water and salt; stir to blend, then cover tightly and set aside 5 minutes. Meanwhile, place sweet potato cubes in 2-quart microwave-safe casserole or bowl and add just enough water to cover cubes.
Cover dish with lid or plastic wrap and microwave on High, 8 minutes, rotating dish after 4 minutes if microwave does not have a carousel.
Uncover and drain potatoes.

title: taco casserole (stove top style)
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with onion and season to taste. Drain.
Put meat mixture into kettle with taco seasoning, mushrooms and pinto beans; do not drain juice.
Heat well, then add tortilla chips (crushed) and grated cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
May be served with picante sauce.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes.
Chop onions and green pepper quite fine.
Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.

title: al's wild meat chili
directions: Grind rabbit and squirrel meat.
Cook until tender and brown. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Add water slowly while stirring.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine pie filling, gelatin and water; add 2 packets of Sweet 'N Low and butter flavoring.
Cook until thick and clear.
Cool. Fold in sliced strawberries that have been sprinkled with 2 packets of Sweet 'N Low.
Pour in pie shell.

title: muffins
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together with pastry fork or blender, then stir just until all ingredients are blended.
Fill greased cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Serve hot with butter and jam.

title: party snack sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into quarter size balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
These can be frozen, then baked when needed.
Recipe can be doubled if needed.

title: beef steak potato scallops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat stew meat with flour.
Salt and pepper meat.
Melt shortening in skillet, brown meat.
Add onions, cook and stir until onions are tender.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice steak in 1/4-inch slices.
Cook steak in oil in large skillet until brown.
Stir in tomato, green pepper, soy sauce, sugar, garlic salt, pepper and ginger.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and consomme.
Stir into steak mixture.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over hot rice.

title: deep dish cavitini
directions: Put sausage in kettle. Add 2 cups hot water. Simmer until cooked. Add basil, peppers, onions and garlic salt. Cook 15 minutes. Cut sausage in bite size pieces.

title: pasole (hominy)
directions: Fry pork slowly until done.
Add hominy, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Add onion and green chiles.
Simmer until thickened.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour well.
Add melted margarine.
Add enough evaporated milk to make the mix real soft.
Pour enough of mix to cover bottom of pan about 1 inch deep.
Put berries on top of mix; then cover berries with the remaining mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: chocolate chip applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add applesauce, vanilla and a little cinnamon.
Stir together flour, salt, soda and cocoa. Add to other ingredients.
Sprinkle over top the chocolate chips, sugar and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 cake pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Mix chicken, celery,
walnuts and mushrooms.
Mix cream cheese, chives, margarine, lemon
pepper
and
thyme.
Add
to first mixture.
Roll out
2 packages Pillsbury crescent rolls. Put heaping
tablespoonfuls of mixture on dough and fold ends over. Dip in melted butter, then seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Serve with chicken gravy.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine egg, milk, soup, 2/3 cup cracker crumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in corn, onion and pimiento; mix well.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Toss butter with remaining crumbs; sprinkle atop corn mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; let cool a little and stir in 7-Up.
Drain pineapple (save juice) and fold pineapple, marshmallows and bananas into gelatin.
Pour into large flat pan. Chill until firm.
Add toppings and chill overnight.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
In oven, melt shortening and butter in baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture. Place chicken, skin side down, in shortening and butter.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until tender.

title: tomato and eggs
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and celery until onions become transparent.
Add tomatoes and cook gently until mixture dries a little.
Drop eggs into mixture and stir slightly.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover for 10 minutes.
May be served hot or cold.

title: blueberry puffed pancake
directions: Divide the melted butter into 3 individual ramekins. Place a dozen or so blueberries into each ramekin. Combine the rest of the ingredients and beat until fluffy. Divide equally between the 3 ramekins. Bake at 425°, until browned, approximately 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve as quickly as possible. They will deflate after they sit.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Beat the egg well, then add the 6 Tbsp. of cold water. Measure the water carefully.
Add the oil and salt and whisk to together.
Mix the baking powder and flour together.
Blend the two mixes into a smooth batter quickly.
Drop into boiling stew and cover continuing to boil for 15-20 minutes.
Try to resist the urge to peek too often, the dumplings will rise and produce a light tender crust.
A cold draught will cause them to fall. They can also be served as a dessert by cooking in boiling water and served with pancake syrup or jam drizzled over them.

title: vegetable stuffed squash
directions: Wash squash thoroughly and place in a large saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 to 6 minutes or until tender but still firm.
Drain and cool slightly.
Trim off steams and cut squash in half lengthwise. Gently scoop out pulp, leaving firm shell.
Drain and chop pulp. Combine pulp and remaining ingredients.
Place squash shells in a 19 x 9-inch baking dish; spoon vegetable mixture into shells. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Contains 68 calories per serving.

title: zesty nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brush both sides of tortillas with oil. Quarter each tortilla. Transfer to ungreased baking sheet, and bake uncovered until crisp (about 10 minutes). In a small saucepan, combine tomato sauce, garlic, cumin, chili powder and cloves. Cover and bring to boil over high heat (about 1 minute). Reduce heat. Simmer uncovered, stirring, until sauce thickens slightly (about 5 minutes). Top tortillas with tomato sauce and peppers, then with mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, until cheeses have melted (about 3 minutes). Sprinkle with parsley and serve warm.

title: cereal yogurt bars
directions: Combine cereal, 3/4 cup flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Pat half mixture into greased 8-inch square pan.
Combine yogurt, egg and 2 tablespoons flour. Spread over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: In large saucepan, cook ground beef and onion until onion is tender and ground beef is no longer pink.
Drain fat from meat. Add the remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf and garlic toe.
Serve over hot, drained spaghetti noodles.
Top each serving with grated Cheddar cheese.
Leftovers are great!

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in eggs and flavorings.
Stir in buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 1/3 hours.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Combine brown sugar and 2/3 cup margarine.
Stir in egg, sour milk and vanilla and mix well.
Sift the baking soda and flour together and stir in margarine mix.
Stir in rhubarb and nuts. Pour into well-oiled loaf pans.
Combine the 1/2 cup of white sugar, cinnamon and 1 tablespoon melted margarine and sprinkle over top of loaves.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 40 minutes or until done.
Don't overbake.
Let stand for 2 or 3 minutes, then remove from pans and cool.

title: ripe olive dip
directions: Mash cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers or party bread.

title: easy brunch
directions: Beat eggs and milk, then add salt and onion flakes.
Spread bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour egg mixture over all items in the pan.
Cover pan with foil and either refrigerate overnight or bake now.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then remove foil and continue baking for an additional 5 minutes or until eggs are completely cooked.
Cut into squares to serve 6 to 8.

title: mock mousse
directions: In a small bowl, blend sour cream and frosting; beat at highest speed until smooth and creamy.
Spoon into serving dishes. Chill 30 minutes before serving.
Store leftovers, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk; knead well.
Roll dough on flat floured surface.
Spread sausage over dough.
Roll into loaf and slice.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: banana split pie
directions: Layer 1:
Beat together with mixer, butter, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla until custard like (5 minutes).
Pour over graham cracker crust.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Blend above ingredients.
Fill up to line with regular milk.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 14-inch pan.
Spread coconut and pecans on bottom.
Mix cake according to package.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Melt butter or oleo; add cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Spread over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerated yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Stir in oil, eggs and 4 cups flour; mix well.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and knead in bowl.
Cover with greased foil.
Refrigerate 4 hours or up to one week.
Take out as much as you want to bake at a time.

title: savory baked spinach
directions: Combine cooked, well-drained spinach with all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: barb's fresh peach pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; let stand 1 hour.
Mix the cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Gradually pour syrup from peaches; cook until thick and clear.
Mix with peaches, stirring gently.
Place peach mixture on bottom crust of pie shell.
Roll top crust and place over peaches.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° for 30 minutes. Best if sets to cool for awhile.

title: cheese pie
directions: Put cheese, Worcestershire, salt and dry mustard in pan.
Heat on low, stirring constantly until melted.
Beat eggs until foamy. Add to cheese mixture gradually; stirring constantly.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.
Decorate with tomatoes, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Bake at 375° around 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine apples, cinnamon, salt and water.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
In bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soup, chicken and onion powder into ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix remaining ingredients and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture; sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 30 minutes until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: spam casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, mix in butter, onions, green pepper, celery soup, Spam and black pepper.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: janet's #1 broccoli casserole
directions: Combine cream of mushroom soup, onions, cheese, mayonnaise and 1/2 of bread crumbs together.
Mix in broccoli.
Place in baking dish.
Spread remaining bread crumbs over the ingredients.
Pour the melted butter over the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave for 15 minutes.

title: skillet italian meat loaf
directions: Wet bread and squeeze out by hand excess water.
Mix all ingredients together, crushing Italian seasoning between fingers. Then form large patties by hand.
Put in large skillet and cook slowly until browned on both sides.
Pour off excess grease.
Mix 1 cup ketchup and 1 cup water.
Pour over meat; cover and let simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Thicken gravy with 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 cup water (will not use all of it) or use your own thickening. Wonderful for summer when you do not want to use oven.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with cheese and rice.
Thaw broccoli and combine with cheese mixture in a casserole dish.
Evenly distribute butter on the top and place in oven until bubbly, approximately 45 minutes.

title: quick sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; remove 1/4 inch from ends.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine cucumbers, red pepper, onion and garlic in a large bowl.
Add salt; stir well.
Pack ice over cucumbers; cover and let stand 3 hours.
Remove garlic; rinse and drain.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute bacon slowly and pour off most of the fat.
Brown chopped onion and beef in hot fat.
Add salt.
Wash rice, drain and add with 1 1/2 cups tomato juice and paprika to meat.
Pour into greased casserole and bake in moderate oven (350°) until rice is tender, about 30 minutes, adding more tomato juice as it is absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut head of lettuce and cauliflower in large pieces.
Cut onion up; put with lettuce and cauliflower.
Dice and fry bacon (drain).
Mix bacon with mayo, sugar and Parmesan cheese; spread over salad and chill overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
In 3 quarts of boiling water, add potatoes, carrots and celery.
When near done, add noodles, rice, cabbage, stew seasoning, chopped tomatoes and paste.
Then add hamburger.
Keep plenty of juice in pan.

title: franny's pound cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Beat butter until creamy; gradually add sugar, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream (begin and end with flour).
Beat well; add lemon and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Put in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes on rack.
Remove; dust with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: poppy chicken
directions: Cook chicken; cool and debone.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Stir together yogurt and soup and pour over chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine crushed crackers, poppy seed and melted margarine in a bowl.
Crumble this mixture over the chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on label in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Remove from oven and while still hot poke holes in it and slowly pour cream of coconut over (shake can well before opening). Then slowly pour condensed milk over cake. Chill, then spread LaCreme topping over all. Sprinkle with almonds.

title: berry pink cloud
directions: Use a wide-mouth glass gallon jar.
Use very ripe peaches (almost not up to standard, they will be so ripe).
Wash and place in jar.
Do not break the skins.
Use as many as will fit without forcing.
Add 3 cups sugar.
Fill to within 1/2-inch of top with either vodka or gin (about 1 liter).
I use a cheap brand since it takes so much.
Screw lid on.
(You can cover with plastic wrap before putting lid on if you like.)

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 300° in well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes, until done.
Start with a cool oven.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: holli's crumbly vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables for 5 minutes and drain well.
Place vegetables in a 9 x 13 pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over top of vegetables.
Bake at 350 for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Melt butter; add onion and saute.
Add broccoli; stir and simmer for a few minutes.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz and simmer again.
Add Minute rice; stir and put in buttered baking dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: quick cucs
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain well but do not rinse.

title: pfeferouladen
directions: Have round steak sliced very thin, less than 1/4-inch.
Cut into strips 2-inches wide and 4-inches long.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread lightly with mustard.

title: selma's virginia pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and continue to cream until perfectly smooth, about 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended.
Add cake flour a little at a time.
Slowly add milk, then flavorings.

Add baking powder last. (This is a lighter and better blended mixture if electric mixer is used.) Grease and flour a large Bundt pan (or line with foil and grease and flour a large tube pan or a small tube pan and a loaf pan).
Pour cake batter into pans and place in a cold oven.
Turn temperature to 325° or 350° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Do not jar cake or remove from oven too soon.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Can be served as a base for strawberry shortcake.
Toasted pound cake slices spread with butter make an excellent breakfast treat.
Freezes well.
Serves 15.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Roll in crushed pecans.

title: apricot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and milk.
Mix well, then add preserves, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in sheet pan at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in oiled 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: avocado eggs
directions: Mash yolks of eggs with fork.
Add the cheese, 3/4 avocado, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stuff the egg whites.
Slice remaining avocado thinly.
Put thin slice of avocado on top of eggs.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Soak overnight.
Bake in oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Put rhubarb in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix sugar and flour together and scatter over rhubarb.
Cream brown sugar and oleo together.
Add oats, cinnamon, nutmeg and 4 tablespoons flour and mix together until crumbly.
Spread on rhubarb.
Bake for 38 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: tapioca fruit salad
directions: Take juice from pineapple and oranges plus enough water to equal 3 1/2 cups.
Heat to a boil.
Add tapioca until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over fruit and mix.
Garnish with maraschino cherries or strawberries.
Refrigerate at least several hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl of mixer; add butter, eggs, nuts and bananas. Beat on low speed until all blended, about 1 minute. Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 1 hour or until done.
Makes 1 medium sized loaf.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; boil for 2 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Drop onto sheet of wax paper; let cool.

title: spiders
directions: Melt in a double boiler all contents but noodles.
When melted, pour over chow mein noodles.
Spoon out onto a greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and eat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Boil chicken with onion; debone chicken and save broth.
Mix and brown oleo and flour.
Add milk, mushrooms, turmeric and broth.
Add rice and chicken.
Place in casserole dish or baking pan.
Sprinkle with or lay sliced cheese on top. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: holly's festive fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and salt in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stirring in peanut butter until melted.
Add marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Fold in M&M's.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool at room temperature.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions, using only 3 cups of milk for the 2 packages.
Add Cool Whip and set aside.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed in oblong pan.
While still warm, use fork to punch holes in cake.
Mix 1 cup hot water and jello.
Pour over warm cake.
After cake has cooled, spread Cool Whip over cake.
Spread thawed strawberries over Cool Whip.

title: sesame asparagus
directions: Cook asparagus according to package directions.
Drain well. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Gently stir in mushrooms, butter and lemon juice.
Cook until heated through.
Turn mixture into serving bowl; sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: aunt mimi's squares(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread walnuts in 15 x 10 x 1-inch in jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides.
Place in oven to toast nuts.
Stir frequently.
Remove nuts after they are golden brown, approximately 10 minutes.

title: vanilla butternut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk, alternating and ending with flour.
Fold in flavoring by hand. Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°. Start in cold oven.
Do not open door while baking.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust; bake at 325° for approximately 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: ham-it-up crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place ham slices on rectangles.
Spread ham slices with mustard; sprinkle with cheese. Starting at shortest side, roll up each rectangle.
Press edges to seal.
Coat rolls with sesame seed.
Cut each of the 4 rolls into 5 slices, forming 20 slices.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Add creamed corn; mix together. Add remaining ingredients.
Fry in butter-flavored Crisco at 300° in electric skillet.

title: potato cakes
directions: Grate raw potatoes together with onions.
Add eggs, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Drop into heated fat in frying pan or griddle. Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: candy cane popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn in a warm oven.
Butter sides of saucepan. Combine sugar, syrup, vinegar, 1 1/2 cups water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook until hard boil stage; stir in vanilla.
Pour slowly over popcorn; mix well.
Butter hands; shape into balls around candy canes.

title: crescent cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Dip marshmallows in melted margarine, then generously coat with sugar-cinnamon mixture. Starting at the large end, wrap the crescent roll around 1 marshmallow completely covering it.
Squeeze edges tightly to seal. Dip in margarine and then in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place in muffin tin.
Place muffin tin on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown at 250° to 350°.
Serve immediately.

title: chili soup
directions: Fry hamburger with salt, pepper and onions.
Chop hamburger with a food chopper.
Add to other juice.
Heat and serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake in a tube or Bundt pan at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir well sugar, water and white syrup all the time.
Cook to crack stage.
Then add peanuts and butter.
Stir well.
Cook until syrup becomes golden brown, a must.
Peanuts will smell roasted. Stir all the while.
Then remove from fire.
Quickly add vanilla. Stir quickly.
Add soda.
Stir well and quickly.
Have two cookie sheets buttered ahead of time.
Pour half of the mixture on one pan and the other half on the other pan.
Work quickly.
Do not spread mixture.
Let cool completely and break into pieces.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook sliced zucchini and chopped onion in boiling water 5 minutes.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrots. Fold in drained zucchini and onion.
Mix stuffing and butter together.
Spread half of stuffing in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan or baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until heated through.

title: lentil stew
directions: Rinse lentils.
Pour lentils into deep pot; add all other ingredients and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer until lentils are cooked, about 1 1/2 hours.
Season to taste.
Serve with salad and crusty bread.
Makes 8 servings.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix well:
flour, sugar, bran, soda and salt.
Add beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Batter will keep 6 weeks.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all but the last 2 ingredients.
Form into loaf and top with brown sugar and ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook noodles; drain.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix and pat in bottom of long glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes; let cool.

title: garbage bread
directions: Roll out bread dough to form a rectangle.
Pour pizza sauce on dough and spread.
Add pepperoni, onion and Mozzarella cheese. Roll up bread and pinch edges.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°. Let cool for 15 minutes.
Slice bread.
(You can substitute with cubed chicken, broccoli and Cheddar cheese, or make up your own Garbage Bread.)

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mash 1 pint strawberries; add sugar.
Bring to a boil and thicken with cornstarch mixed with a bit of water.
Allow to cool. Slice 1 pint strawberries into pie shell.
Pour thickened berries over uncooked berries.
Chill; serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cranberry salad
directions: When grinding cranberries, use coarse chopper blade.
Use fine blade for orange peel.
Dice apples very fine.
Mix together with nuts, sugar and pineapple.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate and let set.

title: pumpkin-raisin muffins
directions: Combine pumpkin, brown sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir in raisins. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 15 muffins.

title: california crusty coconut pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut.
Let stand while mixing the next part. Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add soaked coconut and vanilla. Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; then bake at 350° for 20 minutes until set.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix together first four ingredients and pour over oyster crackers.
Toss so that the crackers are well coated with seasonings.
Store in an airtight container.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Use as dip for summer fruits.

title: banana bars
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.

title: pinwheels(prep time 15 minutes before refrigerating)
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch square pan with cooking spray.
Mix gelatin and water in 1 1/2 to 2-quart microwavable bowl and microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Add marshmallows; zap 1 minute or until marshmallows are puffed and almost melted.
Stir mixture slowly until marshmallows are completely melted and mixture is smooth.
(Creamy layer, floats on top.)
Pour into greased pan.
Refrigerate 45 minutes or until set.
Starting at one edge, roll up tightly.
With seam side down, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 pieces.

title: dorothy mcnamara's brownies
directions: Beat oleo and sugar well.
Add the eggs and beat.
Add the chocolate syrup.
Combine flour and baking powder and stir into chocolate mixture, adding chopped nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in jelly roll pan.
Frost cooled brownies (recipe follows).

title: iowa brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; slowly add syrup, then eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add flour.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp lo mein
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add shrimp; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove.
Add chicken broth and the next 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles, onion and frozen vegetables.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in shrimp.
In small bowl mix cornstarch and water.
Gradually stir into mixture in skillet.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Strain juice from cherries and pineapple (makes about 9 to 10 ounces).
Heat and pour over jello.
Add cherries, pineapple, nuts and celery.
At the very last, add the Coca-Cola.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions.
Brown in butter.
Add bouillon cubes.
Fill 4-quart pan 3/4 full of water.
Bring all of these to a boil, then simmer at least 1/2 an hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Dice chicken into a mixing bowl.
Add onion, garlic salt, chili powder and tomatoes.
Reserve 1 cup of cheese for topping. Add remaining cheese to chicken mixture.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine oil, eggs, sugar and pumpkin.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and add liquids.
Stir until all is moist. Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour,
or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: peppermint creams
directions: Spread a large sheet of wax paper on a work surface.

In a pan, combine the sugar, corn syrup, milk and cream of tartar. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Increase heat to moderate and continue cooking, stirring constantly, until soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat and set aside for 3 minutes to cool slightly.
Beat in peppermint. Continue beating until creamy.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: country ham with red eye gravy
directions: In a large nonstick skillet over medium heat; cook ham slices 2 - 3 minutes per side. Remove to serving platter and keep warm. Add coffee and cornstarch mixture to skillet, stirring to scrape up brown bits. Bring to boil over medium heat; boil 2 minutes. Spoon over ham.

title: cornell barbecued chicken
directions: Beat egg; add oil and beat again.
Add vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Place broiler halves over coals.
Turn and baste every 5 to 10 minutes.
Baste lightly at first.
Increase as cooking time goes on.
Chicken will be ready in about an hour. Serves 10.

title: chicken drumettes
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder and pepper.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook until done.
Turn occasionally.
Remove chicken and drain on paper towels.
Keep warm.
Pour off drippings.
Reserve 1/4 cup in skillet.
Combine onion soup mix and water.
Stir into drippings. Cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Combine sour cream and chicken soup.
Add to drippings mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir often. Serve over split biscuits.

title: hamburger stroganoff(good to the last drop)
directions: Brown meat in 2 teaspoons butter.
Stir in flour and next 4 ingredients.
Add 1 cup water and mushrooms with liquid.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Combine sour cream with milk; stir into meat mixture.
Add wine (optional) and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Arrange chops in a shallow baking pan.
Place on each a slice of onion and green pepper; pour over tomato sauce.
Bake in moderate 325° oven for about one hour.
Throw in some small-to-medium baking potatoes (or start them a half-hour earlier).

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pecans) and shape into one or two balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: plum cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs, one at a time, beating each time. Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add plums, then pears. Bake in flat pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugars, milk and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Cook until mixture comes to the soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla.
After marshmallows melt, remove from heat and stir mixture until it begins to thicken, approximately 1 minute.
Pour onto buttered dish.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: herb roasted potatoes and peppers
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/3-inch slices.
Cut red and green peppers into chunks.
Cut onion into chunks.
Heat oven to 450°.
Mix potatoes, peppers and onion in shallow baking pan.
Add dressing; toss to coat.
Bake 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Process in blender until drink is fully mixed and ice cubes have been crushed.

title: orange crush pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add orange crush alternately with flour.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let cake cool.

title: corn bread
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, beat together eggs, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture and stir just until batter is smooth (do not overbeat).
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican salsa salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Cut 1 package of the cookie dough into triangles as if you were making cookies. (Cut into 9 slices, then quarter each slice.) Place these pieces on end in bottom of pan.
Don't pat or squeeze together; leave openings between pieces of dough.
Beat cream cheese, eggs , sugar and vanilla.
Pour mixture over cookie dough.
Cut second package of cookie dough and arrange just as before, but make this layer on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 32 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes, then refrigerate.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: gemischter salat
directions: The tomato, cucumber and celeriac for this dish should be prepared in the morning.
The salad can be quickly assembled just before dinner.

title: stir-fried asparagus
directions: Cut asparagus into 3-inch pieces.
Heat oil to very hot in 12-inch skillet.
Add asparagus and stir quickly and frequently until evenly coated with oil.
Sprinkle with salt and continue stir-frying for about 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Serves 6. Contains 55 calories per serving.

title: carrot-raisin apple salad
directions: Wash carrots, apples and rinse raisins.
Scrape carrots and peel apples.
Grate carrots and apples.
Add raisins.
Pour orange juice and vinegar over all.
Add spices and mix with spoon or fork.
Set aside in refrigerator covered.

title: spicy orange salad
directions: Drain oranges, reserving juice and add enough water to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Place in saucepan; add spices and salt and simmer for 10 minutes.
Let steep for 10 minutes; strain.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water mixture; add 2 cups cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in oranges and walnuts. Pour in mold; chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: heavenly hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Stir in sugar gradually, about 4 tablespoons at a time, and be sure that the sugar is moistened after each addition.
Mixture will become very thick and quite dry.
Add salt and slowly stir in the evaporated milk a little at a time.
Stir until smooth and satiny.
Serve hot.
This makes 2 cups of sauce and it may be stored in a covered refrigerator jar and heated in a double boiler as you need.
For a thinner sauce, slowly add 1 or 2 tablespoons evaporated milk as you heat it.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Discard the juice from the dill pickles.
Slice each kosher dill into quarters lengthwise.
Put half of them into original jar and the other half into the empty jar with a tight lid.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool.
Pierce cake with large 2 prong utility fork at 1/2 inch intervals.
Spoon Jell-O over cake.
Mix instant vanilla pudding into Cool Whip.
Use pudding (dry) as it comes from box.
Spread Cool Whip mixture over cake.
Spoon on cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients (except nuts). Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Good with ice cream, whipped cream or plain.

title: squash muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Place in muffin pans and bake at 400°.
Makes 1 dozen large muffins.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Saute the veggies along with pepper and garlic flakes.
Can also brown bulk sausage, however, this is optional.
Place half of the cheese in the bottom of pie crust.
Mix the veggies with eggs and cream.
Pour into crust.
Top with remaining Cheddar cheese. Bake at 400° until golden, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican rice casserole
directions: Cook beef; drain.
Mix beef, taco seasoning, tomato sauce, cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes, rice, salt and corn.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole pan.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pork chop marmalade
directions: Flour pork chops.
Brown on both sides.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Pour mixture over chops in frying pan. Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
(Use very little oil when browning chops.)

title: grits
directions: Boil water in heavy saucepan.
Add salt.
Stir grits slowly into water.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: rice krispie muffins
directions: Add milk to Rice Krispies and let stand until soft.
When soft add egg and shortening; beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar, then combine dry and wet mixtures.
Bake in greased muffin pan at 400° about 25 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients in a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan. Pour liquid ingredients into pan; mix well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: banana devil's food cake
directions: Melt oleo, brown sugar, eggs, bananas and bitter chocolate. Cool.
Add flour mix (flour, baking soda, salt, vanilla and buttermilk) and milk alternately into first mix.
Bake in 2 layer pans 30 minutes at 350°.
Use mashed bananas between layers and ice with your favorite chocolate icing.
Very good if left set overnight.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix ingredients in a heavy pan, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 14 ounce peanut butter. Beat and pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.

title: shower punch
directions: Put ginger ale and pineapple juice in punch bowl.
Mix.
Add sherbet a little while before serving.
Makes 20 (3 ounce) servings.

title: old fashion egg pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Add eggs (well beaten).
Add butter and milk.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until pie is set.
Pie will not brown on bottom unless you sit it in another pan.

title: white pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (or follow crust package directions). Brown sausage, crumble it and drain.
Sprinkle sausage, onion, pepper, mushrooms, olives and sliced artichoke hearts on crust. Add cheese to the top.
Sprinkle garlic powder and olive oil over the whole pizza.
Bake until cheese is melted and crust cooked through, about 15 to 20 minutes (you may have to cook longer if crust or toppings are extra thick).
Serves 4.

title: pot roast
directions: Mix dry soup and cream of mushroom soup with 1 can of water in a large (I use a 5 litre Corning Ware dish) baking dish.
Place roast in soup mixture.
Add carrots, onions, and potatoes.
Cook covered for approximately 2 hours in a 350 degree oven.

title: nanny's peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, peanuts, syrup and water.
Cook until light brown and peanuts stop popping.
Add margarine and baking soda. Pour into greased cookie sheet pan.
Do not spread, just pour. When cool, break into pieces.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and pour sugar over the berries; let set 10 minutes.
Add all the other ingredients.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Brown meat until crumbly.
Drain fat.
Add taco mix, onion and tomatoes.
Cook over low heat a few minutes.
Combine eggs, milk and 1 cup of the corn.
Add cornbread mix and blend well.
Pour 1/2 of the batter in a 15 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch casserole.
Top with beef mixture, cheese slices and remaining corn.
Cover with remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corned beef sandwich spread
directions: Mix together and add enough mayonnaise to spread evenly on bread.
Serve toasted.
Keep spread in refrigerator.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in boiling water. Let set until a soft jell in refrigerator. Then add drained pineapple and apricots; may add some sugar, if desired. Mix all together and place in refrigerator until set.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread, butter bread slices and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Cook sausage until brown and crumbled. Drain, then spoon sausage over buttered bread.
Next, sprinkle shredded cheese over sausage.

title: quick chicken curry
directions: Cook onion in butter or margarine.
Add the cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Stir in the sour cream and curry powder.
Add the cubed turkey or chicken and heat. Garnish with snipped parsley.
Serve over fluffy hot cooked rice. Offer curry condiments of chutney, raisins, toasted slivered almonds, sliced green onion, and mixed pickles.

title: **bean salad
directions: Cover vegetables with sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper. Mix well and let stand at least two hours before serving.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Let cheese get warm and cut into pieces.
Place in large mixing bowl; add pimento, including juice.
Mix until smooth.
Add mayonnaise and thoroughly mix.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in large bowl. Mix last 3 ingredients well and spread on top of layered salad, covering completely to the end of the bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Toss immediately before serving.

title: veal chops with mustard sage sauce
directions: Melt butter with oil in medium skillet over medium-high heat. Lightly sprinkle dried sage and pepper.
Add to skillet and cook until brown, about 5 minutes per side.
Reduce heat and cook to desired doneness, about 1 minute per side for medium rare. Transfer veal to a plate and keep warm.
Add shallots to same skillet; add broth, 1 tablespoon minced sage and mustard.
Boil until thick.
Add half and half and boil until thickness to sauce consistency.
Mix in the remaining sage (minced) and any juices exuded by veal.
Place 1 chop on each plate and spoon sauce over. Garnish with fresh sage leaves and serve.

title: cheddar and jalapeno dip
directions: In a blender or food processor, whip all ingredients together until smooth and light.
If too thick, thin with a little milk. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving. Makes about 4 1/2 cups.
Wonderful with tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, pumpkin and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pans at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 60 bars.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; beat eggs.
Add all ingredients to melted butter and eggs.
Bake in uncooked pie shell in 300° oven for 45 minutes. Test until fairly firm in center.

title: grandma davis' 8-minute light 'n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes. Add ice cubes and stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whip or spoon, blend in Cool Whip.
Whip until smooth.
Fold in sliced strawberries and chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound. Spoon into crust.
Chill for 2 hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip and strawberries, if desired.

title: onion surprise
directions: Cut onions into quarter. Arrange in dish.
Place dab of butter on each piece of onion. Sprinkle bouillon over onions. Cover and cook in Microwave on high for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix; put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugars and mix well.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to mixture.
Blend in gum drops, coconut and oatmeal.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil, garlic salt, dill seed,
and salad dressing mix. Pour over oyster crackers. Let stand 1 hour. Stir and enjoy!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir vegetable soup mix and sour cream until blended.
Cover; chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: ice cream pie
directions: This is one of
those
recipes where you adjust amounts according to the size of pie plate you are using.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt; add buttermilk, eggs, oil and cereal.
Place in muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Add coconut to pudding mix and cook according to package directions.
Add pineapple to cooked coconut-pudding mix.
Pour into crust and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: raised donuts
directions: Scald milk and pour over shortening.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add about 3 1/2 cups of flour (not too stiff a dough).
Let rise an hour or more, stirring down once.
Roll out and cut or twist.
Let rise on board for 30 to 45 minutes.
Fry, top side down.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients except reserved cheese in an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with reserved cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 12.
May be frozen and reheated in microwave.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in egg, vanilla and salt.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Stir in coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with floured bottom of a glass.
Sprinkle with additional coconut, if desired. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown around edges. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: sunday pot roast
directions: Season to taste before cooking or after.
In large roaster, place roast.
Layer potatoes, carrots and onions.
Cover partially with water.
Place in 350° oven for 2 to 3 1/2 hours.
I usually put this in oven before Sunday School and upon arriving home from church, dinner is prepared.
Serve with coleslaw and rolls.

title: fruit dump cake
directions: Don't stir. Place ingredients one at a time in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: buckwheat waffles
directions: Heat waffle iron while mixing ingredients together.
Mix ingredients, adding milk slowly to mixture until batter is right. Make sure iron is hot before pouring batter in.
Serve with hot maple syrup!

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water about 30 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Beat cream cheese in mixer until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients until combined.
Spoon mixture into a lightly buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions, adding 1 teaspoon salt.
Drain cauliflower, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat; blend in flour.
Stir in milk and reserved liquid; cook until thickened stirring constantly. Season sauce with remaining salt.
Spread 2/3 cup sauce in casserole; add cauliflower.
Pour 2/3 cup sauce over cauliflower; sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Arrange eggs in casserole over cheese; cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ciambelone
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy; then add eggs, all but
2 egg whites (save for tops), then add flour alternating with milk.
Add
juice
and whiskey.
Beat 2 egg whites until foamy, but
not
stiff, for top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Use a round pan with a hole in the center.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. This is an Italian cake.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain the beans and place them in long 9 x 13-inch dish. Preheat oven to 350°.
Put can of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk in saucepan.
Slice the package of Velveeta cheese and add to saucepan.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Turn heat to low and melt the cheese until bubbly.
Pour this over the beans.
Put onion rings on top of this and bake in 350° oven until all of it bubbles, approximately 25 minutes.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cream in butter.
Add well beaten eggs and milk.
Add vanilla and bake in uncooked pie shell for 45 minutes at 375° in preheated oven.

title: green chili and cream cheese dip
directions: Mash cream cheese, adding milk to thin slightly.
Add green chilies, onion and garlic.
Add Worcestershire sauce to taste and more milk, if necessary, to thin to dipping consistency.
Allow to stand at least 1 hour before serving.
If refrigerated, allow to return to room temperature for dipping.

title: ground bologna salad
directions: Grind bologna.
Add all other ingredients; mix thoroughly. Refrigerate.
Use as sandwich or serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in margarine until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add chicken broth and milk, stirring constantly. Add diced potatoes and broccoli. Sprinkle in nutmeg.
Cook over medium-low heat 25 to 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Pour into serving bowls and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: appetizer hamburgers
directions: Brown the two meats together.
Drain, then add rest of ingredients.
Mix and spread on rye bread.
Can be frozen on a cookie sheet, then put in plastic bags.
Heat under broiler until hot.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt the butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in top section of double boiler over hot but not boiling water, stirring frequently, until blended.
Remove from heat and add cereal, stirring until well coated with butterscotch mixture.
Press half of the cereal mixture into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill in refrigerator while preparing fudge mixture.

title: hot fudge pudding(my children love this pudding.)
directions: Blend all together and pour into well-greased pan. Combine 1 cup brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa and sprinkle over batter. Pour 1 3/4 cups boiling water over all. Bake at 350° until done.

title: egg drop soup(chinese)
directions: Beat eggs along with sherry.
Place in saucepan the chicken broth plus water, salt and ginger slice.
Bring to boil and remove ginger slice.
Pour beaten eggs/sherry in thin stream into boiling soup while stirring.
Remove from heat immediately.
Garnish with green onion.
Serve hot.

title: exotic chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice and three kinds of soup together; place in large roaster pan.
Pour melted butter on top.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 275°.

title: yankee strawberry shortcake
directions: Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Place in a large, flat Pyrex dish.
Prepare jello using only 2 cups of boiling water.
When dissolved, add ice cream and strawberries; mix well.
Pour over cake pieces.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion and celery; add Veg-All, soup and chicken.
Pour into pie shell; cover with other pie shell and pierce for steam holes.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, salt, pepper, eggs, toast crumbs and onion.
Form into small balls.
Fry bacon.
Brown meatballs in bacon grease. Drain fat. Add chili sauce, cranberry sauce and crumbled bacon. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
These meatballs are very good. Serve them at parties using toothpicks.

title: party cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat by hand until well blended. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: creamy chicken broccoli noodles
directions: In a saucepan, cook noodles by package directions. Add seasoning packet. Drain off most of the liquid. Stir in the cream of mushroom soup and milk. Add chicken and broccoli.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often. Remove from heat and stir in tomatoes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender, cover and process until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50-55 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: romaine salad with strawberries
directions: Peel kiwi; cut into half lengthwise and cut each half into quarters.
Toss with romaine and strawberries.
Combine vinegar, jam and oil in a bowl.
Stir well with a wire whisk.
Pour over salad, tossing gently to coat.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Take cream cheese out of refrigerator a few hours before to soften.
Cook noodles and set aside.
Put cream cheese together with sour cream.
Cook beef, onion, oregano, garlic and salt to taste.
Brown, then drain off grease.
After browning, add tomato sauce and simmer.
Layer in casserole noodles, meat and cream cheese.
Cover with grated cheese and bake 1/2 hour at 350° (1 hour if frozen).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender in salted water (drain).
Mix carrots, onions and pimentos.
Stir well.
Add sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Mix well.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Put a layer of stuffing mix in casserole, then squash mix, then another layer of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chinese hot sour soup
directions: Partially
freeze
meat for easier slicing.
Slice pork thinly into
bite-size pieces.
In 3-quart saucepan cook pork pieces in hot oil until lightly browned.
Drain and set aside.

title: bacon bread sticks(microwave)
directions: Wrap bacon slices around bread sticks.
Sprinkle or dip into Parmesan cheese.
Cook on High power for 6 to 8 minutes, depending on number cooking or until desired doneness is reached for bacon. Cut into bite size pieces.
Serve as appetizer.

title: meatball sauce
directions: Mix the ingredients and beat until well blended. Add cooked meatballs.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar.
Press into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1 inch cubes.
Bring water to a boil in large saucepan.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Set aside potatoes.
Measure 1 cup cooking liquid, adding water if necessary; set aside.
Peel and finely chop onion.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion to saucepan; cook, stirring frequently, until onion is translucent and tender, but not brown.
Add flour to sauce pan; season with red and black pepper to taste.
Cook 3-4 minutes.
Gradually add potatoes, reserved 1 cup cooking liquid, milk and sugar to onion mixture in sauce pan.
Add cheese and diced ham.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: crepes(these are also called pollachinglas by my grandmother.)
directions: Beat eggs with mixer until blended. Add flour, salt, butter and milk.

title: dressing
directions: Bake at 450°.
Cook until golden brown.
It depends on your oven as to length of time.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Remove from oven and while it is still warm, dust with powdered sugar.

title: seasoned onion rice
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onion and saute 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Coat a 1 1/2-quart casserole with cooking spray.
Add rice mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Bake shell for 10 minutes.
Set aside.
In bowl, combine eggs, sour cream, salt and Worcestershire.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Pour mix into shell and bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Gives 8 small servings.
Makes a lunch for 4 people along with a green salad.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix well. Leave out of fridge all day (8 to 12 hours) or until very bubbly. Remove 1 cup and return to fridge. Keep in fridge 3 to 5 days and feed with same ingredients. If not making bread, throw 1 cup away after feeding. Always feed 3 to 5 days.

title: pepperoni and cheese bread
directions: Measure the warm water into a warm bowl.
Sprinkle the yeast on the water and stir until dissolved.
Add the sugar, salt, butter and three cups of flour and beat until smooth (with flat beater if you have a KitchenAid or equivalent).
Then add the remaining flour, a cup at a time (with the dough hook) to make a soft dough.

title: mom's plain sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Stir in beaten egg and vanilla.
Add milk alternately with flour which has been sifted with salt and baking powder.
Drop on cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar. Bake in a 400° oven just until edges start to brown a little.

title: layered salad
directions: In large bowl, place lettuce, then a layer of green pepper, then the onion, then the peas.
Combine mayo and sugar.
Pour over peas.
Sprinkle cheese over top, then bacon bits.
Make and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Cover tightly.
Will keep for several days.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: You can also add celery, onion and broccoli.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook until smooth on low to medium heat.
Cook broccoli as directed on package, along with grated carrot.
Combine milk mixture and broccoli. Stir in cheese until melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix strawberry cake mix according to directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While hot, pour Eagle Brand milk over hot cake and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with fresh strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together ingredients and place in crust.
Bake at 350° until coconut is brown and pie is firm when shaken.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Cook turnips in boiling water until just tender.
Drain. Saute in butter the onion, green pepper and celery until tender. Sprinkle with flour and cook 1 minute.
Add milk and stir until thickened.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Combine cheese sauce with turnips.
Place in baking dish and top with crumbs. Brown under broiler.
May be prepared ahead and placed under broiler just before serving.

title: roasted garlic turkey with pasta
directions: Roast garlic in olive oil in oven set at 400° for 10 minutes or just until golden; let cool.
Puree pesto, balsamic vinegar and honey with the cooled garlic and oil.
Reserve 1/2 of mixture as marinade for the turkey.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all
together
in one large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: striped delight dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/3 cup melted butter; press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of the thawed Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Add to mixed dry ingredients.
Add butter.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: a variation of larry's oven-fried potatoes *
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges.
Place in single layer skin side down on cookie sheet.
Spray with olive oil. Sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until crisp.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix together sugar, milk, flour and baking powder.
After this is mixed, spread over margarine in baking dish.
Pour over batter (berries or any other fruit of your choice).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups and sour cream.
Prepare dressing per directions.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until dressing is brown, about 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: popcorn rabbit
directions: Keep popcorn warm in oven.
Melt the marshmallows with butter. Mix everything together.
Shape into rabbit on cookie sheet. Decorate with jelly beans.
Cool.
Eat.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and salt thoroughly in a saucepan.

Add water and place over low heat, stir until gelatine is dissolved. Remove from heat and stir in undiluted lemonade concentrate, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Fold into whipped evaporated milk.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: cherry banana punch
directions: Blend all together.
Make 1 gallon of base.
Freeze at least 2 days prior to serving.
Stir to keep ice chips forming once a day. Before serving, add 1 quart 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: cranberry top sweets
directions: Parboil potatoes until tender.
Cut in half and put in baking dish.
Pour cranberry sauce over top.
Sprinkle with sugar and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: oatmeal scones
directions: Mix flour, oats, salt and baking powder.
Cut in margarine until mixture is mealy looking.
Mix in milk just until mixture is moist.
Pat out in well greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.
It tastes best if you spread butter on top of the whole thing as soon as you take it out of the oven.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Pour into a baked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.

title: betty crocker's banana-sour cream bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, sour cream, margarine and eggs in large bowl.
Beat in bananas and vanilla.
Beat in flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased and floured jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: salsa bread
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan and drain. Cut biscuits in half and mix in large bowl with salsa. Mix in ground beef. Bake in 9x13 pan for 45 min. at 350 degrees in preheated oven. Remove pan and sprinkle on cheese. Return to oven until cheese is melted (about 2 min).

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in dates and walnuts, and then eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
While warm, cut into bars. Cool and remove from pan.
Roll in sifted confectioners sugar. Makes 3 dozen.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased casserole. Bake at 350° until browned on top or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: olive casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 40 minutes or until rice is tender.
Toss slightly with a fork several times during the last 15 minutes of cooking or until liquid is almost all absorbed.
Yields 6 3/4 cup servings.

title: uncle steve's favorite apple crumb pie
directions: Arrange apple slices in the 9-inch pie crust. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apple slices. Sift 1/2 cup sugar and flour. Cut in margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dietetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is boiled away.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Blend in flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans overnight, drain and set aside.
Saute onions till tender.
Add green chilies and the 3 spices, cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add beans and chicken broth, bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken, 1 c. cheese, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, uncovered and reduce heat to simmer for 10 minutes stirring often.
To serve top with cheese.
Yields: 13 cups.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Fill greased cake pans 1/2 full.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook ground meat and onions until brown.
Drain all liquid off meat. Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread meat in pie plate.
Sprinkle grated cheese over meat.
Mix Bisquick, eggs and milk for 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute by hand mixer.
Pour over meat and onions.
Bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center, comes out clean.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash squash and slice or chop.
Add onion and sugar and boil in small amount of water until tender.
Drain well and let cool.
Stir in slightly beaten egg, cheese, salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with stuffing mix and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy okra dish
directions: Melt butter in medium frying pan.
Add whole okra pods and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Cover and simmer until okra is tender (about 10 to 15 minutes).

title: peach delight
directions: Melt butter in large dish.
Pour peaches in butter.
Stir other ingredients together to make a batter.
Pour around and over peaches.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
You can also use blueberries or cherries.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan for 5 minutes to 245°.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped popcorn in very large bowl or kettle; mix evenly.
Spread out on 2 large well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, cool slightly and pour onto wax paper (on countertop).
Break into pieces as it cools.

title: kathryn's oleo rolls
directions: Mix oleo and milk.
Wait until lukewarm.
Add yeast, eggs, sugar, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Take out and divide in half.
Roll in circle and cut in wedges. Roll like crescent rolls.
Let rise 4 hours.
Bake about 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Brush with melted butter.

title: white chili
directions: Wash beans; place in large pot.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans.
Let soak.
Drain beans, return to pot.
Add broth and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat, simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add chicken and next 5 ingredients, cook, covered, 30 minutes longer.
Spoon into bowls, top with cheese.

title: chicken casserole #3
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix in half of the stuffing mix.
Mix chicken, soups and onion; pour over stuffing. Add other half of stuffing; pour on 1 1/2 cups chicken broth. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Layer the ingredients at listed in a large shallow bowl or large platter with sides. Top with tomato and olives.

title: heirloom chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, 1 at a time. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into shell and bake at 375° about 50 minutes.
