title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer in a glass bowl in this order:
lettuce (in bite size), celery, eggs, peas, onion, peppers and crumbled bacon (may substitute bacon bits).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix.
Bake in a greased casserole dish for 25 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Last 15 minutes of baking, add crumbled Ritz crackers. Sprinkle with extra cheese (optional).
Makes 4 servings.

title: pasta pie surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Crumble crackers in a 9-inch pie pan. Take 1/2 cup melted butter and mix with crumbs.
Pat down to make crust.
Put rest of the butter in a skillet; add onions and saute until clear.
Pour onions over crackers.
Pur vegetables over onions.
Place noodles over all, then top with the cheese.
In a small bowl, beat eggs well and mix milk and seasonings into egg. Pour over all and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and golden brown.
Slice as a pie and serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin mousse
directions: Mix all together in blender. Fold in 1/4 recipe of Dream Whip. Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving. Serve with bananas (sliced), nuts and vanilla wafers or serve on cake or warm gingerbread.

title: quick and easy pies
directions: Start with ice cream, frozen yogurt, sherbet or instant pudding.
Stir in 1 cup of fruit pieces or cookie pieces or combination of raisins and nuts.
Fill graham crust and chill or freeze until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
To eggs add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Blend in oil.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Sift all remaining dry ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into greased loaf pan or two (1-pound) coffee cans, well-greased. Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar on top (optional).
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan(s), then turn onto rack.
Cool completely. Wrap in lightweight foil.
Store in refrigerator or store in freezer.

title: mom's bologna gravy
directions: Fry bologna in margarine until nicely browned.
Dice the bologna in the skillet and stir in the flour.
When completely mixed, gradually add milk and stir; bringing to a boil and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
It is good over boiled or mashed potatoes or bread.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook these ingredients in a pan over medium heat until mixture is thick like pie filling.
Then blend until crumbly 1 cup powdered sugar and 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Put 2/3 cup of this mixture in bottom of cooked pie crust.
Pour cooked pie filling over this.
Beat 3 egg whites with 1/3 cup sugar until fluffy and stiff.
Do not add sugar until egg whites are frothy.
Put this meringue on top
of pie filling and then sprinkle remainder of peanut butter mixture on top of meringue and brown in medium oven.

title: cream pies(chocolate, coconut or banana)
directions: Mix dry ingredients with a little of the milk after heated. Blend well; add rest of milk .
Cook first 4 ingredients in top of double boiler, stirring until thick.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Add a little of the mixture to the beaten egg yolks.
Stir well.
Pour back into hot mixture.
Cook a few minutes longer.
Add margarine and vanilla. Pour into pie shell; cover with meringue and brown.

title: magic fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of baking dish.
Mix milk, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Pour over butter, but do not stir.
Pour fruit over batter (undrained).
Sprinkle fruit with extra sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 375°.
Add cinnamon to peaches or
apples.
Add a little almond flavoring to cherries.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put pumpkin into blender to make smooth, then mix all ingredients.
Put into pie shells and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes, or until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: irish cream ala jackie keegan
directions: Mix in blender and refrigerate. Can be "drunk" the next day. Tastes better after a few days in refrigerator.

title: never fail pastry
directions: Blend flour, Crisco and salt with mixer.
Add milk with vinegar poured in it.
Mix and knead like bread, adding more flour as needed.
Roll out.
Makes 2 crusts.
Very rich.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form dough into balls and roll into white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Do not overcook or cookies will turn hard.

title: coconut, pecan apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan. Set aside. Blend eggs, oil and sugar until creamy. Add flour, a little at a time.
Blend well. Batter will be stiff. Fold in apples, coconut and pecans.
Pour into a tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from pan after about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Arrange banana slices on bottom of crust; set aside.
Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute or until well blended.
Pour mixture at once into crust. Cover with whipped topping.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: basic oven meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in milk, crumbs, onion and salt.
Add meat and mix well.
Chill.
With wet hands, shape meat mixture into 6 dozen meatballs.
Bake in two 15 x 10-inch pans at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Place meatballs on another baking pan. Cool.
Can be frozen.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pie shell for 7 to 8 minutes. Remove from oven and lower heat to 350°.
Cut 6 slices of cheese into strips and set aside.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream the margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon extract and flour.
When smooth, fold in 7-Up.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Combine mix, Cool Whip and egg.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls in the sugar.
Coat.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter and sugar; mix well.
Stir in beaten egg, water and vanilla.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet. Yields about 4 dozen.

title: cran-orange delight cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes before removing to a wire rack.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Season with salt and pepper. Coat each side with corn meal.
Heat oil in a skillet.
Fry tomatoes on each side until lightly brown.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast with 1/2 cup warm water. Beat eggs. Add cake mix and yeast. Add salt to flour. Add the flour and the 2 cups warm water alternately. Add more flour if too sticky. Form ball in greased bowl. Let rise until double (approximately 1 hour). Roll out dough. Brush with margarine. Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon. Roll up and cut into 1-inch pieces. Put in well-greased pan. Let rise. Bake in preheated 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes. Cover with Saran Wrap immediately when removed from oven. Cool and then cover with icing.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Boil broccoli; drain.
Add soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper. Simmer and serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Yield:
1 serving.
Carbohydrate 14 g, protein 8 g, fat 9 g, calories 169.
One serving = 1 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: cheese and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and add milk until soupy.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir about 15 minutes into cooking time.
Add grated cheese to top of dish the last 5 to 10 minutes of cooking.

title: apple pudding dessert(heart smart)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until well blended and moist. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Serve with lite Cool Whip.
Recipe is from the Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with mixer.

Add cake mix, lemon pudding, oil, water, nuts and poppy seed. Put in tube pan (greased) or 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. While hot, poke holes with fork in the cake and pour icing over the cake.

title: lazy stew
directions: Cook all together.
Cover and thicken for 45 minutes.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: sugar-free spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in closed container.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill crock-pot half full with apples.
Add sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Finish filling crock-pot with apples.
Cook overnight or approximately 4 or 5 hours on high.
Use a hand mixer and beat until smooth.
If it is not thick, cook a little while without the lid.
Seal in sterilized jars.
When using another kind of apples, cut the sugar into about half, if the apples are sweet.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix everything but apples.
Save 1/3 cup peanuts to put on top.
Mix in apples that have been soaking in the pineapple juice. Drain off juice.

title: chili noodle casserole
directions: Cook ground beef with onions, then drain.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix macaroni with beef mixture and add the tomato puree (or sauce or whole tomatoes).
Place mixture in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Slices of cheese can be placed on top, if desired, for the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: 15 minute brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat for 15 minutes.
Use pepper and Tabasco sauce to taste.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Cream sugar and mayonnaise together.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with water.
Add flavoring and mix well. Pour batter in a prepared 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done when toothpick comes out dry.
This cake will be very moist.
Frost with a vanilla frosting.

title: real devil's food cake
directions: Start oven at 375° or moderate.
Grease bottoms and sides of 3 (8-inch) cake pans and dust with flour.
Sift cake flour; measure it carefully and sift again with soda and salt.
Cream margarine in bowl until soft and airy.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Beat batter hard after the addition of each egg.
Put chocolate in measuring cup and melt over boiling water.
When melted, add to batter and mix thoroughly.
Sift about 1/3 of the flour into batter.
Stir well and add 1/3 of the buttermilk.
Repeat, ending with flour.
Mix in vanilla and boiling water.
Pour batter into cake pans.
Don't be alarmed at the thinness of the batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn cake upside-down on cake rack.
Spread frosting between layers and on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine cubed beef, salt, pepper and flour; toss until meat is coated.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine to heated skillet; brown meat quickly and remove.
Brown mushrooms, garlic and onion in skillet. Add beef, vegetables and beef stock to stock pot.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Add sour cream.
Continue on medium heat until heated through.
Do not boil.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Brown hamburger and drain. Mix hamburger, potatoes, and soups in 13x9 inch baking dish. Bake until potatoes are tender (about one hour).

title: tomato cheese dinner
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Let the bread raise until double in size.
Roll out and spread with melted butter or oleo, then sprinkle with cinnamon, then with brown sugar. Roll dough up together like jelly roll. Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Let rise a little, then bake for 15 or 20 minutes. Spread with glaze.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package instructions.
Drain, rinse, and cool.
Slice and chop all vegetables (wash also).
Add Italian Seasoning.
Mix in spaghetti.
Add Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: cinnamon sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add cake mix and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Put on lightly floured surface and knead 3 to 5 minutes.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning enough to grease top of dough.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Punch down dough.
Place on floured surface.
Roll to desired thickness.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar mixture.
Roll like jelly roll.
Cut in 1-inch slices and place in lightly greased pan.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: chicken salad pockets
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken, celery, raisins and green onions.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; blend well.

Pour dressing over chicken mixture; mix well. Arrange 1/4 of spinach leaves and 1/4 of apple slices in each pocket with the pieces extending slightly over edge of pocket. Spoon 1/4 of chicken salad mixture into each pocket.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery; season lightly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place in baking pan or casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine 1/2 cake mix, water, eggs, margarine and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Blend in remaining cake mix.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, let sit in refrigerator several hours for best flavor.

title: mable's favorite
directions: Mix everything but ice cream into punch bowl.
Just before serving, add ice cream.

title: corn relish
directions: Remove kernels from corn cobs.
Put the corn, cucumbers, red peppers, sweet peppers and celery through a coarse meat chopper. Combine the sugar, salt, turmeric, mustard, vinegar and water; bring to a boil and boil for 15 minutes.
Stir in vegetables. Add mustard seed and celery seed.
Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: sherried chicken
directions: In a 3-quart baking dish, place chicken breasts and mushrooms. Mix together chicken soup, sherry and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and baking soda. Add bananas, flour, salt and vanilla.
Bake in a loaf or square pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar, water and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir egg yolks into whites.
Sift dry ingredients into mixture a little at a time and add to mixture.
Pour on jelly roll pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Lay on towel and roll up.
Cool and unroll and put jelly in between.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend all together all ingredients except corn flakes and margarine.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole at 350° for 45 minutes. During last 20 minutes of cooking, top with a mixture of the corn flakes or cornbread stuffing and margarine.

title: country kitchen meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pat into the shape of a loaf.
Top with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel rolls(make evening before baking)
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle pecans to cover bottom of pan.
Arrange frozen dough over pecans.
Sprinkle pudding over dough.
Melt margarine, syrup, sugars and cinnamon just until sugars dissolve.
Drizzle over rolls.
Cover with wet towel in cool place overnight.

title: grape salad
directions: Soften cream cheese, then beat, adding about 1/4 cup lemon juice to look like stiff whipped cream.
Add about 1 cup powdered sugar (a sweet and sour taste).
Add grapes and nuts.
Chill.

title: broccoli-cheese and rice
directions: Cook broccoli slightly and drain.
In a large bowl, mix broccoli, chicken soup, rice, Cheez Whiz and vegetables, which have been
sauteed	in
margarine.	Put
in
lightly
buttered baking dish and bake
for
to
30 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned on edges.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce.
When hot, add steak sauce and catsup to meat mixture.
Put pinto beans in an 8 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Pour meat mixture on top of beans.
Top with corn muffin mix (mix as directed on package). Bake at 400° until corn bread has baked and a nice brown color. Serve with a salad and you have a good meal.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Heat 1 1/2 cups of cooking oil on medium heat in pan.
Using a teaspoon, dip hush puppies into oil and cook until golden brown.

title: holiday breakfast bread
directions: Blend together eggs and oil; then set aside.

title: five pounds of fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and oleo and bring to boil.
Cook 8 minutes to "soft ball" stage.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and spread to cool in buttered dishes.
When cool, cut into small squares.
Store in wax paper-lined tightly covered containers in refrigerator.

title: apple roll-ups
directions: Bring
to
boil
in
saucepan.
Pour over dough mix and bake in a 350° oven until golden brown (45 minutes to 1 hour). If
too dry, boil more water, a little sugar and butter; pour over
and let cook a little longer.
Keep checking during the 45
minutes to
see
if
getting
too dry.
Go ahead and pour mixture on anytime.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Top with crushed cornflakes, sugar, cinnamon, nuts and 1/4 pound margarine. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: beef crumble and gravy
directions: Brown beef and minced onion in hot shortening.
Add salt, pepper and Bisquick.
Continue browning; slowly stir in milk and water.
Serve over toast or pancakes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Bottom Layer:
Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in crushed pineapple. Put into refrigerator until firm.

title: mushroom appetizer
directions: In medium bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then broil 5 minutes longer, until done.

title: microwave cabbage
directions: Cook all ingredients except cheese in 2-quart casserole, covered on High in microwave for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 minutes.
Stir in cheese and salt.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and raisins; add bacon.
Pour dressing over all and marinate 1 or 2 hours.

title: krispie peanut butter balls
directions: Cream
peanut
butter,
margarine and sugar together in large bowl.
Add
Rice
Krispies
and mix well.
Shape batter into balls.
Melt
chocolate
chips
and paraffin in top of a double boiler.
Dip
balls in melted chocolate and place them on
waxed paper until chocolate is hardened.
Store candies in an airtight container until ready to serve.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients together and frost cake.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce that has been torn into bite-size pieces in bottom of dish. Layer peas (uncooked) and onions. Layer egg, then spread salad dressing on top of these layers.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: onion cucumber relish
directions: In a small bowl or container, stir together the vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Pare cucumbers thinly; run the sharp tines of a fork lengthwise down cucumber to score; slice very thin. Peel onion and slice extremely thin; separate into rings.
Add cucumber and onion to marinade; cover.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving, leaving vegetables in marinade and using a pierced or slotted serving spoon.
There should be about 1 1/2 scant cups cucumber slices and about 2 cups onion rings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients; beat well and bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Stir in the Cool Whip.
Make pudding with milk as directed on package. It does not have to set.
Mix with Cool Whip mixture.

title: peanut and pretzel bark
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt candy coating, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients. Spread into thin layer on 2 aluminum foil-lined baking sheets. Chill 30 minutes or until firm.
Break into chunks.
Store covered at room temperature or in refrigerator.

title: baked rhubarb crunch
directions: In bottom of a greased 9 x 13 pan, thoroughly mix the rhubarb, 1/2 cup sugar, flour and nutmeg. Combine brown sugar, flour, oats and salt in a bowl. Cut in the butter and sprinkle on top of the rhubarb mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until crisp and nicely browned.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats, let stand 20 minutes.
Cream the Crisco, sugar, brown sugar, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and eggs.
Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rum raisin cheddar crock
directions: Soak raisins in rum for 1 hour.
In medium bowl, beat the cheese until fairly smooth (or process in blender or food processor). Add raisins and rum and beat or whip briefly to blend and to chop raisins slightly.
Pack into container and store in refrigerator. Serve with crackers, raw vegetables and fruits. Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: wiggly wiggles
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread into shallow baking pans.
Break up any clumps.
Bake in a preheated (325°) oven 20 to 25 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cool, then store in a tightly covered containers in the refrigerator.

title: milk shake for diabetics
directions: Place all ingredients in electric blender and blend until milk shake foams up and ice cube disappears.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: baked stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix the 2 soups together. Set aside. Brown onion, celery and hamburger in skillet. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, alternate vegetables, the meat, then soups. Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: eggplant vegetable medley
directions: Saute eggplant and garlic in oil until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 8 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: old fashioned potato patties
directions: Fry bacon; crumble.
Reserve fat.
In a bowl, mash cooled potatoes.
Add egg, onion tops, salt and pepper.
Mix well and form into 6 patties.
Over medium heat, fry until brown.
Serve hot.

title: cheese dip
directions: Shred cheese.
Place cheese and other ingredients in a blender, add boiling water last.
Blend until smooth.
Chill.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in large frying pan with 1 stick margarine. Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes, until tender and lightly browned.
In casserole dish (2-quart) place half of the onions. Cover with the cheese of your choice.
Next add crushed Ritz crackers, then repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 325°.

title: okonomiyaki(japanese pizza)
directions: Mix flour, water, eggs, cabbage and scallion together in bowl. Pour 1/2 cup mixture onto hot griddle.
Place sliced meat, shrimp on top.
Cook until edges one dry.
Turn; cook.
Serve with mayonnaise or mustard or soy sauce or ketchup.

title: crab sauce over pasta
directions: Simmer ingredients for 1 hour, then add 1 can of crab meat. Prepare pasta of your choice and serve with crab meat sauce.

title: enchiladas
directions: In saucepan,
combine tomato sauce with next 5 ingredients. Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Steam tortilla on one side and
fill with beans, cheese and green onions.
Roll up and place with
seam side down in baking dish.
Cover with hot sauce
and cheese.
Bake
at
for 20 minutes. Serve garnished with GUACAMOLE.
Serves 6.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, raisins and salt in boiling water for 15 minutes. Remove from stove for 1 hour, then add the remaining ingredients. Cook on top of stove in a heavy pan until thick.
Stir until it boils and thickens.
Serves 10 people.

title: dad's squirrel pie
directions: Boil squirrel in 4 quarts of water with whole cloves and garlic until falling off bone.
Remove from liquid and bone squirrel.
Strain cloves from liquid.

title: sad cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order as given.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: tasty tuna melt
directions: Combine tuna, celery, onion and soup (blended with boiling water).
Spoon on toasted English muffin and top with cheese; broil.

title: plum cake
directions: Combine all together. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Prick with fork so icing will run through.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening and remove from heat. Add brown sugar, mixing well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Add nut meats and chocolate chips. Mixture will be very stiff. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until tested done. Cut into squares when cool. Makes 12 (3 x 3-inch) squares or 48 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon hot fat until just tender.
Combine with next 5 ingredients.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, combine cheese and milk; stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over ham-potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; mix thoroughly and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine chocolate and sugar.
Add cream and butter or butter substitute.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and flavoring.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Place marshmallows on well buttered dish evenly. Pour mixture over them.
Let cool; cut in squares with a sharp knife.

title: frozen banana dessert cups
directions: Puree bananas, strawberries, pineapple, honey and nutmeg in blender until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and almonds.
Line muffin pans with foil cupcake liners.
Fill with banana mixture. Cover and freeze until firm.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in blender all ingredients for 1 minute.
Pour into well-greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is a crustless pie.

title: cream sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour; stir well and add coffee cream (slowly) while stirring.
Continue stirring until you get a thick sauce.
To this sauce can be added mushrooms, shrimp, crabmeat, grated cheese, white wine, lemon juice, egg yellows, etc. or any of these.
(Makes 2 cups.)

title: perfect cookies
directions: Chop Shredded Wheat finely in blender or food processor (will make 3 cups).
In large bowl, combine Shredded Wheat, flours, oats, soda and cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: chicken and dressing scallop
directions: Spread dry stuffing mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup water over stuffing.
Top with chicken.

title: asparagus vinaigrette mimosa(microwave)
directions: Wash asparagus and snap off tough, light colored ends. Measure water into a 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Place spears in dish with bud ends toward center, arranging thickest spears toward outer edges of dish.
Cover dish with plastic wrap and microwave-cook on full power 3 minutes. Turn dish halfway or rearrange spears a bit.
Re-cover and microwave-cook at full power 3 minutes.
Turn dish again, re-cover and microwave about 2 minutes longer or until tender yet still crisp.
Drain liquid from dish.
Combine oil, salt, pepper, sugar, green onions, mustard, parsley and vinegar in small bowl.
Pour dressing evenly over asparagus and marinate in refrigerator, covered, for at least 1 hour, spooning dressing over spears several times.
Place asparagus on serving platter and sprinkle with chopped eggs.

title: pineapple and ham pasta salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
In large bowl, combine pineapple, ham, bell pepper, peas, celery and macaroni.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, onion powder, pepper and dill weed.
Stir dressing into pineapple mixture.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving to allow flavors to blend.
Serves 8.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, 1 1/3 cups water, eggs, oil, 2 cups coconut and nuts.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: chocolate popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Mix popcorn and peanuts in large shallow roasting pan.
Cook sugar, corn syrup and margarine in heavy 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Stir in chocolate.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until chocolate is completely melted and mixture is very thick.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over popcorn; stir to coat well.
Bake for one hour, stirring occasionally.
Pour popcorn in single layer onto cookie sheets or foil; cool.
Store in tightly covered containers.

title: five-alarm salsa
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring all the ingredients to a simmer over medium-low heat, then cook for 5 minutes.
Spoon the salsa into hot, sterilized jars and attach the lids.
Process the jars in a boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Remove from the water and cool at room temperature.

title: sue smith's rhubarb custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk.
Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Stir in eggs and milk.
Mix in rhubarb.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with lattice top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes, until browned.

title: spaghetti
directions: Shape hamburger into meat balls and brown over medium heat. Lower heat and add onion; simmer until brown.
Add tomato soup, salt, pepper, garlic salt, chili powder and paprika to taste. Simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour, covered.
Cook and drain spaghetti. Pour sauce over spaghetti and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serves 4.

title: play dough
directions: Boil water
and salt until bubbly; cool.
Add alum, oil and flour and
knead.
Add desired food coloring.
Can be kept for quite awhile in the refrigerator.

title: belgium salad
directions: Heat to a boil.
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, powdered sugar, oleo, oil and eggs. Add the remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar. Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Dough can also be put through a cookie press and sprinkled with sugar prior to baking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: The day before, cook chicken, cool and remove meat from bones. Cut into bite-size pieces.
Toss with French dressing and marinate overnight.
Add celery and mayonnaise until desired consistency is achieved.
Place into baking dish and spread Cheez Whiz on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Put French fried onions on top and bake for 5 minutes.
"Also good cold the next day!"

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes; prick several times with a fork. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done; let cool. Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out and reserve pulp. Discard shells. Melt butter in a Dutch oven over low heat. Add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in potatoes, salt, pepper, 1 cup cheese, 1/2 cup bacon and 2 tablespoons green onions; cook until heated (do not boil). Stir in sour cream. Cook just until heated (do not boil). Serve with remaining cheese, bacon and green onions. Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook at low temperature for 20 to 25 minutes.
This is enough sauce for 2 pounds of ham.

title: spinach bake
directions: Place chopped spinach in 2-quart casserole dish.
In bowl, combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over spinach. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is hot.

title: grandma cookies
directions: *Do not use Shedd's Spread.
The cookies will never firm up. This is true about any soft margarine.

title: josephines
directions: Toast bread on one side.
Mix butter, chilies and garlic. Spread on untoasted side of bread.
Top with mixture of mayonnaise and grated cheese.
Broil until brown and puffy.
Serve at once.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet,
cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate dough into 8 triangles. Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust, spread evenly with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture evenly into crust.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
If crust becomes too brown, cover with foil during last 10 minutes of baking.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: baked spinach and ham frittata
directions: Beat together eggs, basil and pepper.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in spinach and ham.
Add egg mixture and return to heat.
Cook until egg are set.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Slice onion into thin wedges using as much as you like.
Add salt, pepper and sour cream.
Toss until mixed thoroughly.
Set aside in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.

title: picadillo
directions: Saute peppers, onion and garlic in margarine in a 12-inch nonstick skillet for 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in kidney beans, cumin, red pepper, tomato sauce and raisins.
Cook to thicken slightly, about 10 to 12 minutes over medium-high heat.
Mixture should be saucy.
Serve with low-fat corn muffins.
Together about 450 calories and 8 grams of fat.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Peel and seed avocados.
In large bowl, mash avocados with potato masher or the back of a fork.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
If not serving, immediately cover with plastic wrap, making sure there are no air bubbles between plastic and guacamole.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chipped beef; form into ball and cover with chipped beef.
Keep refrigerated until serving.

title: fresh herbs and shrimp
directions: Heat oil in saute pan, add shrimp and cook until they turn pink.
Remove leaving oil and juices.
Add garlic and cook until soft.
Add wine and reduce mixture by half.
Add lemon juice and heat to a boil.
Remove from heat and whisk in butter until thick. Stir in herbs, season.
Add shrimp and serve over angel hair pasta or parsley rice.
Serves 4 to 6. Great for first courses, lunches and buffets.

title: apple date crisp(an old fashion dessert from germany)
directions: Combine the apples and dates in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. In a small bowl, combine sugar, flour and cinnamon; cut in butter until crumbly. Add nuts; sprinkle over apples. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until the apples are tender. Serve warm. Garnish with apple slices, if desired. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: white chili
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak 8 hours.
Drain beans and return to Dutch oven.
Add broth and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and next 5 ingredients; cover and cook 30 minutes.
Spoon into serving bowls; top each with cheese and a spoonful of salsa.
